00001 // Note: For maximum-speed code, see "Optimizing Code" on the Emscripten wiki, https://github.com/kripken/emscripten/wiki/Optimizing-Code
00002 // Note: Some Emscripten settings may limit the speed of the generated code.
00003 // The Module object: Our interface to the outside world. We import
00004 // and export values on it, and do the work to get that through
00005 // closure compiler if necessary. There are various ways Module can be used:
00006 // 1. Not defined. We create it here
00007 // 2. A function parameter, function(Module) { ..generated code.. }
00008 // 3. pre-run appended it, var Module = {}; ..generated code..
00009 // 4. External script tag defines var Module.
00010 // We need to do an eval in order to handle the closure compiler
00011 // case, where this code here is minified but Module was defined
00012 // elsewhere (e.g. case 4 above). We also need to check if Module
00013 // already exists (e.g. case 3 above).
00014 // Note that if you want to run closure, and also to use Module
00015 // after the generated code, you will need to define   var Module = {};
00016 // before the code. Then that object will be used in the code, and you
00017 // can continue to use Module afterwards as well.
00018 var Module;
00019 if (!Module) Module = eval('(function() { try { return Module || {} } catch(e) { return {} } })()');

00021 (function(Module) {
00022 // Sometimes an existing Module object exists with properties
00023 // meant to overwrite the default module functionality. Here
00024 // we collect those properties and reapply _after_ we configure
00025 // the current environment's defaults to avoid having to be so
00026 // defensive during initialization.
00027 var moduleOverrides = {};
00028 for (var key in Module) {
00029   if (Module.hasOwnProperty(key)) {
00030     moduleOverrides[key] = Module[key];
00031   }

00157   forceAlign: function (target, quantum) {
00158     quantum = quantum || 4;
00159     if (quantum == 1) return target;
00160     if (isNumber(target) && isNumber(quantum)) {
00161       return Math.ceil(target/quantum)*quantum;
00162     } else if (isNumber(quantum) && isPowerOfTwo(quantum)) {
00163       var logg = log2(quantum);
00164       return '((((' +target + ')+' + (quantum-1) + ')>>' + logg + ')<<' + logg + ')';
00165     }
00166     return 'Math.ceil((' + target + ')/' + quantum + ')*' + quantum;
00167   },
00168   isNumberType: function (type) {
00169     return type in Runtime.INT_TYPES || type in Runtime.FLOAT_TYPES;
00170   },
00171   isPointerType: function isPointerType(type) {
00172   return type[type.length-1] == '*';
00173 },
00174   isStructType: function isStructType(type) {
00175   if (isPointerType(type)) return false;
00176   if (isArrayType(type)) return true;
00177   if (/<?{ ?[^}]* ?}>?/.test(type)) return true; // { i32, i8 } etc. - anonymous struct types
00178   // See comment in isStructPointerType()

00183   or64: function (x, y) {
00184     var l = (x | 0) | (y | 0);
00185     var h = (Math.round(x / 4294967296) | Math.round(y / 4294967296)) * 4294967296;

00189     var l = (x | 0) & (y | 0);

00191     return l + h;

00194     var l = (x | 0) ^ (y | 0);

00198   getNativeTypeSize: function (type, quantumSize) {
00199     if (Runtime.QUANTUM_SIZE == 1) return 1;
00200     var size = {
00201       '%i1': 1,
00202       '%i8': 1,
00203       '%i16': 2,
00204       '%i32': 4,
00205       '%i64': 8,
00206       "%float": 4,
00207       "%double": 8
00208     }['%'+type]; // add '%' since float and double confuse Closure compiler as keys, and also spidermonkey as a compiler will remove 's from '_i8' etc
00209     if (!size) {
00210       if (type.charAt(type.length-1) == '*') {
00211         size = Runtime.QUANTUM_SIZE; // A pointer
00212       } else if (type[0] == 'i') {
00213         var bits = parseInt(type.substr(1));
00214         assert(bits % 8 == 0);
00215         size = bits/8;
00216       }
00217     }
00218     return size;
00219   },
00220   getNativeFieldSize: function (type) {
00221     return Math.max(Runtime.getNativeTypeSize(type), Runtime.QUANTUM_SIZE);
00222   },
00223   dedup: function dedup(items, ident) {
00224   var seen = {};
00225   if (ident) {
00226     return items.filter(function(item) {
00227       if (seen[item[ident]]) return false;
00228       seen[item[ident]] = true;
00229       return true;
00230     });
00231   } else {
00232     return items.filter(function(item) {
00233       if (seen[item]) return false;
00234       seen[item] = true;
00235       return true;
00236     });
00237   }

00247   STACK_ALIGN: 8,
00248   getAlignSize: function (type, size, vararg) {
00249     // we align i64s and doubles on 64-bit boundaries, unlike x86
00250     if (type == 'i64' || type == 'double' || vararg) return 8;
00251     if (!type) return Math.min(size, 8); // align structures internally to 64 bits
00252     return Math.min(size || (type ? Runtime.getNativeFieldSize(type) : 0), Runtime.QUANTUM_SIZE);
00253   },
00254   calculateStructAlignment: function calculateStructAlignment(type) {
00255     type.flatSize = 0;
00256     type.alignSize = 0;
00257     var diffs = [];
00258     var prev = -1;
00259     var index = 0;
00260     type.flatIndexes = type.fields.map(function(field) {
00261       index++;
00262       var size, alignSize;
00263       if (Runtime.isNumberType(field) || Runtime.isPointerType(field)) {
00264         size = Runtime.getNativeTypeSize(field); // pack char; char; in structs, also char[X]s.
00265         alignSize = Runtime.getAlignSize(field, size);
00266       } else if (Runtime.isStructType(field)) {
00267         if (field[1] === '0') {
00268           // this is [0 x something]. When inside another structure like here, it must be at the end,
00269           // and it adds no size
00270           // XXX this happens in java-nbody for example... assert(index === type.fields.length, 'zero-length in the middle!');
00271           size = 0;
00272           alignSize = type.alignSize || QUANTUM_SIZE;
00273         } else {
00274           size = Types.types[field].flatSize;
00275           alignSize = Runtime.getAlignSize(null, Types.types[field].alignSize);
00276         }
00277       } else if (field[0] == 'b') {
00278         // bN, large number field, like a [N x i8]
00279         size = field.substr(1)|0;
00280         alignSize = 1;
00281       } else {
00282         throw 'Unclear type in struct: ' + field + ', in ' + type.name_ + ' :: ' + dump(Types.types[type.name_]);
00283       }
00284       if (type.packed) alignSize = 1;
00285       type.alignSize = Math.max(type.alignSize, alignSize);
00286       var curr = Runtime.alignMemory(type.flatSize, alignSize); // if necessary, place this on aligned memory
00287       type.flatSize = curr + size;
00288       if (prev >= 0) {
00289         diffs.push(curr-prev);
00290       }
00291       prev = curr;
00292       return curr;
00293     });
00294     type.flatSize = Runtime.alignMemory(type.flatSize, type.alignSize);
00295     if (diffs.length == 0) {
00296       type.flatFactor = type.flatSize;
00297     } else if (Runtime.dedup(diffs).length == 1) {
00298       type.flatFactor = diffs[0];
00299     }
00300     type.needsFlattening = (type.flatFactor != 1);
00301     return type.flatIndexes;
00302   },
00303   generateStructInfo: function (struct, typeName, offset) {
00304     var type, alignment;
00305     if (typeName) {
00306       offset = offset || 0;
00307       type = (typeof Types === 'undefined' ? Runtime.typeInfo : Types.types)[typeName];
00308       if (!type) return null;
00309       if (type.fields.length != struct.length) {
00310         printErr('Number of named fields must match the type for ' + typeName + ': possibly duplicate struct names. Cannot return structInfo');
00311         return null;
00312       }
00313       alignment = type.flatIndexes;
00314     } else {
00315       var type = { fields: struct.map(function(item) { return item[0] }) };
00316       alignment = Runtime.calculateStructAlignment(type);
00317     }
00318     var ret = {
00319       __size__: type.flatSize
00320     };
00321     if (typeName) {
00322       struct.forEach(function(item, i) {
00323         if (typeof item === 'string') {
00324           ret[item] = alignment[i] + offset;
00325         } else {
00326           // embedded struct
00327           var key;
00328           for (var k in item) key = k;
00329           ret[key] = Runtime.generateStructInfo(item[key], type.fields[i], alignment[i]);
00330         }
00331       });
00332     } else {
00333       struct.forEach(function(item, i) {
00334         ret[item[1]] = alignment[i];
00335       });
00336     }
00337     return ret;
00338   },

00344     } else {
00345       return Module['dynCall_' + sig].call(null, ptr);
00346     }

00378   UTF8Processor: function () {
00379     var buffer = [];
00380     var needed = 0;
00381     this.processCChar = function (code) {
00382       code = code & 0xff;
00383       if (needed) {
00384         buffer.push(code);
00385         needed--;
00386       }
00387       if (buffer.length == 0) {
00388         if (code < 128) return String.fromCharCode(code);
00389         buffer.push(code);
00390         if (code > 191 && code < 224) {
00391           needed = 1;
00392         } else {
00393           needed = 2;
00394         }
00395         return '';
00396       }
00397       if (needed > 0) return '';
00398       var c1 = buffer[0];
00399       var c2 = buffer[1];
00400       var c3 = buffer[2];
00401       var ret;
00402       if (c1 > 191 && c1 < 224) {
00403         ret = String.fromCharCode(((c1 & 31) << 6) | (c2 & 63));
00404       } else {
00405         ret = String.fromCharCode(((c1 & 15) << 12) | ((c2 & 63) << 6) | (c3 & 63));
00406       }
00407       buffer.length = 0;
00408       return ret;
00409     }
00410     this.processJSString = function(string) {
00411       string = unescape(encodeURIComponent(string));
00412       var ret = [];
00413       for (var i = 0; i < string.length; i++) {
00414         ret.push(string.charCodeAt(i));
00415       }
00416       return ret;
00417     }
00418   },

00420   staticAlloc: function (size) { var ret = STATICTOP;STATICTOP = (STATICTOP + size)|0;STATICTOP = ((((STATICTOP)+7)>>3)<<3); return ret; },

00422   alignMemory: function (size,quantum) { var ret = size = Math.ceil((size)/(quantum ? quantum : 8))*(quantum ? quantum : 8); return ret; },

00444 var globalScope = this;
00445 // C calling interface. A convenient way to call C functions (in C files, or
00446 // defined with extern "C").
00447 //
00448 // Note: LLVM optimizations can inline and remove functions, after which you will not be
00449 //       able to call them. Closure can also do so. To avoid that, add your function to
00450 //       the exports using something like
00451 //
00452 //         -s EXPORTED_FUNCTIONS='["_main", "_myfunc"]'
00453 //
00454 // @param ident      The name of the C function (note that C++ functions will be name-mangled - use extern "C")
00455 // @param returnType The return type of the function, one of the JS types 'number', 'string' or 'array' (use 'number' for any C pointer, and
00456 //                   'array' for JavaScript arrays and typed arrays; note that arrays are 8-bit).
00457 // @param argTypes   An array of the types of arguments for the function (if there are no arguments, this can be ommitted). Types are as in returnType,
00458 //                   except that 'array' is not possible (there is no way for us to know the length of the array)
00459 // @param args       An array of the arguments to the function, as native JS values (as in returnType)
00460 //                   Note that string arguments will be stored on the stack (the JS string will become a C string on the stack).
00461 // @return           The return value, as a native JS value (as in returnType)
00462 function ccall(ident, returnType, argTypes, args) {
00463   return ccallFunc(getCFunc(ident), returnType, argTypes, args);
00464 }
00465 Module["ccall"] = ccall;
00466 // Returns the C function with a specified identifier (for C++, you need to do manual name mangling)
00467 function getCFunc(ident) {
00468   try {
00469     var func = Module['_' + ident]; // closure exported function
00470     if (!func) func = eval('_' + ident); // explicit lookup
00471   } catch(e) {
00472   }
00473   assert(func, 'Cannot call unknown function ' + ident + ' (perhaps LLVM optimizations or closure removed it?)');
00474   return func;
00475 }
00476 // Internal function that does a C call using a function, not an identifier
00477 function ccallFunc(func, returnType, argTypes, args) {
00478   var stack = 0;
00479   function toC(value, type) {
00480     if (type == 'string') {
00481       if (value === null || value === undefined || value === 0) return 0; // null string
00482       if (!stack) stack = Runtime.stackSave();
00483       var ret = Runtime.stackAlloc(value.length+1);
00484       writeStringToMemory(value, ret);
00485       return ret;
00486     } else if (type == 'array') {
00487       if (!stack) stack = Runtime.stackSave();
00488       var ret = Runtime.stackAlloc(value.length);
00489       writeArrayToMemory(value, ret);
00490       return ret;
00491     }
00492     return value;
00493   }
00494   function fromC(value, type) {
00495     if (type == 'string') {
00496       return Pointer_stringify(value);
00497     }
00498     assert(type != 'array');
00499     return value;
00500   }
00501   var i = 0;
00502   var cArgs = args ? args.map(function(arg) {
00503     return toC(arg, argTypes[i++]);
00504   }) : [];
00505   var ret = fromC(func.apply(null, cArgs), returnType);
00506   if (stack) Runtime.stackRestore(stack);
00507   return ret;
00508 }
00509 // Returns a native JS wrapper for a C function. This is similar to ccall, but
00510 // returns a function you can call repeatedly in a normal way. For example:
00511 //
00512 //   var my_function = cwrap('my_c_function', 'number', ['number', 'number']);
00513 //   alert(my_function(5, 22));
00514 //   alert(my_function(99, 12));
00515 //
00516 function cwrap(ident, returnType, argTypes) {
00517   var func = getCFunc(ident);
00518   return function() {
00519     return ccallFunc(func, returnType, argTypes, Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments));
00520   }
00521 }
00522 Module["cwrap"] = cwrap;
00523 // Sets a value in memory in a dynamic way at run-time. Uses the
00524 // type data. This is the same as makeSetValue, except that
00525 // makeSetValue is done at compile-time and generates the needed
00526 // code then, whereas this function picks the right code at
00527 // run-time.
00528 // Note that setValue and getValue only do *aligned* writes and reads!
00529 // Note that ccall uses JS types as for defining types, while setValue and
00530 // getValue need LLVM types ('i8', 'i32') - this is a lower-level operation
00531 function setValue(ptr, value, type, noSafe) {
00532   type = type || 'i8';
00533   if (type.charAt(type.length-1) === '*') type = 'i32'; // pointers are 32-bit
00534     switch(type) {
00535       case 'i1': HEAP8[(ptr)]=value; break;
00536       case 'i8': HEAP8[(ptr)]=value; break;
00537       case 'i16': HEAP16[((ptr)>>1)]=value; break;
00538       case 'i32': HEAP32[((ptr)>>2)]=value; break;
00539       case 'i64': (tempI64 = [value>>>0,((Math.min((+(Math.floor((value)/(+(4294967296))))), (+(4294967295))))|0)>>>0],HEAP32[((ptr)>>2)]=tempI64[0],HEAP32[(((ptr)+(4))>>2)]=tempI64[1]); break;
00540       case 'float': HEAPF32[((ptr)>>2)]=value; break;
00541       case 'double': HEAPF64[((ptr)>>3)]=value; break;
00542       default: abort('invalid type for setValue: ' + type);
00543     }
00544 }
00545 Module['setValue'] = setValue;
00546 // Parallel to setValue.
00547 function getValue(ptr, type, noSafe) {
00548   type = type || 'i8';
00549   if (type.charAt(type.length-1) === '*') type = 'i32'; // pointers are 32-bit
00550     switch(type) {
00551       case 'i1': return HEAP8[(ptr)];
00552       case 'i8': return HEAP8[(ptr)];
00553       case 'i16': return HEAP16[((ptr)>>1)];
00554       case 'i32': return HEAP32[((ptr)>>2)];
00555       case 'i64': return HEAP32[((ptr)>>2)];
00556       case 'float': return HEAPF32[((ptr)>>2)];
00557       case 'double': return HEAPF64[((ptr)>>3)];
00558       default: abort('invalid type for setValue: ' + type);
00559     }
00560   return null;
00561 }
00562 Module['getValue'] = getValue;
00563 var ALLOC_NORMAL = 0; // Tries to use _malloc()
00564 var ALLOC_STACK = 1; // Lives for the duration of the current function call
00565 var ALLOC_STATIC = 2; // Cannot be freed
00566 var ALLOC_DYNAMIC = 3; // Cannot be freed except through sbrk
00567 var ALLOC_NONE = 4; // Do not allocate
00568 Module['ALLOC_NORMAL'] = ALLOC_NORMAL;
00569 Module['ALLOC_STACK'] = ALLOC_STACK;
00570 Module['ALLOC_STATIC'] = ALLOC_STATIC;
00571 Module['ALLOC_DYNAMIC'] = ALLOC_DYNAMIC;
00572 Module['ALLOC_NONE'] = ALLOC_NONE;
00573 // allocate(): This is for internal use. You can use it yourself as well, but the interface
00574 //             is a little tricky (see docs right below). The reason is that it is optimized
00575 //             for multiple syntaxes to save space in generated code. So you should
00576 //             normally not use allocate(), and instead allocate memory using _malloc(),
00577 //             initialize it with setValue(), and so forth.
00578 // @slab: An array of data, or a number. If a number, then the size of the block to allocate,
00579 //        in *bytes* (note that this is sometimes confusing: the next parameter does not
00580 //        affect this!)
00581 // @types: Either an array of types, one for each byte (or 0 if no type at that position),
00582 //         or a single type which is used for the entire block. This only matters if there
00583 //         is initial data - if @slab is a number, then this does not matter at all and is
00584 //         ignored.
00585 // @allocator: How to allocate memory, see ALLOC_*
00586 function allocate(slab, types, allocator, ptr) {
00587   var zeroinit, size;
00588   if (typeof slab === 'number') {
00589     zeroinit = true;
00590     size = slab;
00591   } else {
00592     zeroinit = false;
00593     size = slab.length;
00594   }
00595   var singleType = typeof types === 'string' ? types : null;
00596   var ret;
00597   if (allocator == ALLOC_NONE) {
00598     ret = ptr;
00599   } else {
00600     ret = [_malloc, Runtime.stackAlloc, Runtime.staticAlloc, Runtime.dynamicAlloc][allocator === undefined ? ALLOC_STATIC : allocator](Math.max(size, singleType ? 1 : types.length));
00601   }
00602   if (zeroinit) {
00603     var ptr = ret, stop;
00604     assert((ret & 3) == 0);
00605     stop = ret + (size & ~3);
00606     for (; ptr < stop; ptr += 4) {
00607       HEAP32[((ptr)>>2)]=0;
00608     }
00609     stop = ret + size;
00610     while (ptr < stop) {
00611       HEAP8[((ptr++)|0)]=0;
00612     }
00613     return ret;
00614   }
00615   if (singleType === 'i8') {
00616     if (slab.subarray || slab.slice) {
00617       HEAPU8.set(slab, ret);
00618     } else {
00619       HEAPU8.set(new Uint8Array(slab), ret);
00620     }
00621     return ret;
00622   }
00623   var i = 0, type, typeSize, previousType;
00624   while (i < size) {
00625     var curr = slab[i];
00626     if (typeof curr === 'function') {
00627       curr = Runtime.getFunctionIndex(curr);
00628     }
00629     type = singleType || types[i];
00630     if (type === 0) {
00631       i++;
00632       continue;
00633     }
00634     if (type == 'i64') type = 'i32'; // special case: we have one i32 here, and one i32 later
00635     setValue(ret+i, curr, type);
00636     // no need to look up size unless type changes, so cache it
00637     if (previousType !== type) {
00638       typeSize = Runtime.getNativeTypeSize(type);
00639       previousType = type;
00640     }
00641     i += typeSize;
00642   }
00643   return ret;
00644 }
00645 Module['allocate'] = allocate;
00646 function Pointer_stringify(ptr, /* optional */ length) {
00647   // Find the length, and check for UTF while doing so
00648   var hasUtf = false;
00649   var t;
00650   var i = 0;
00651   while (1) {
00652     t = HEAPU8[(((ptr)+(i))|0)];
00653     if (t >= 128) hasUtf = true;
00654     else if (t == 0 && !length) break;
00655     i++;
00656     if (length && i == length) break;
00657   }
00658   if (!length) length = i;
00659   var ret = '';
00660   if (!hasUtf) {
00661     var MAX_CHUNK = 1024; // split up into chunks, because .apply on a huge string can overflow the stack
00662     var curr;
00663     while (length > 0) {
00664       curr = String.fromCharCode.apply(String, HEAPU8.subarray(ptr, ptr + Math.min(length, MAX_CHUNK)));
00665       ret = ret ? ret + curr : curr;
00666       ptr += MAX_CHUNK;
00667       length -= MAX_CHUNK;
00668     }
00669     return ret;
00670   }
00671   var utf8 = new Runtime.UTF8Processor();
00672   for (i = 0; i < length; i++) {
00673     t = HEAPU8[(((ptr)+(i))|0)];
00674     ret += utf8.processCChar(t);
00675   }
00676   return ret;
00677 }
00678 Module['Pointer_stringify'] = Pointer_stringify;

00720 function callRuntimeCallbacks(callbacks) {
00721   while(callbacks.length > 0) {
00722     var callback = callbacks.shift();
00723     if (typeof callback == 'function') {
00724       callback();
00725       continue;
00726     }
00727     var func = callback.func;
00728     if (typeof func === 'number') {
00729       if (callback.arg === undefined) {
00730         Runtime.dynCall('v', func);
00731       } else {
00732         Runtime.dynCall('vi', func, [callback.arg]);
00733       }
00734     } else {
00735       func(callback.arg === undefined ? null : callback.arg);
00736     }
00737   }
00738 }
00739 var __ATPRERUN__  = []; // functions called before the runtime is initialized
00740 var __ATINIT__    = []; // functions called during startup
00741 var __ATMAIN__    = []; // functions called when main() is to be run
00742 var __ATEXIT__    = []; // functions called during shutdown
00743 var __ATPOSTRUN__ = []; // functions called after the runtime has exited
00744 var runtimeInitialized = false;
00745 function preRun() {
00746   // compatibility - merge in anything from Module['preRun'] at this time
00747   if (Module['preRun']) {
00748     if (typeof Module['preRun'] == 'function') Module['preRun'] = [Module['preRun']];
00749     while (Module['preRun'].length) {
00750       addOnPreRun(Module['preRun'].shift());
00751     }
00752   }
00753   callRuntimeCallbacks(__ATPRERUN__);
00754 }
00755 function ensureInitRuntime() {
00756   if (runtimeInitialized) return;
00757   runtimeInitialized = true;
00758   callRuntimeCallbacks(__ATINIT__);
00759 }
00760 function preMain() {
00761   callRuntimeCallbacks(__ATMAIN__);
00762 }
00763 function exitRuntime() {
00764   callRuntimeCallbacks(__ATEXIT__);
00765 }
00766 function postRun() {
00767   // compatibility - merge in anything from Module['postRun'] at this time
00768   if (Module['postRun']) {
00769     if (typeof Module['postRun'] == 'function') Module['postRun'] = [Module['postRun']];
00770     while (Module['postRun'].length) {
00771       addOnPostRun(Module['postRun'].shift());
00772     }
00773   }
00774   callRuntimeCallbacks(__ATPOSTRUN__);
00775 }
00776 function addOnPreRun(cb) {
00777   __ATPRERUN__.unshift(cb);
00778 }
00779 Module['addOnPreRun'] = Module.addOnPreRun = addOnPreRun;
00780 function addOnInit(cb) {
00781   __ATINIT__.unshift(cb);
00782 }
00783 Module['addOnInit'] = Module.addOnInit = addOnInit;
00784 function addOnPreMain(cb) {
00785   __ATMAIN__.unshift(cb);
00786 }
00787 Module['addOnPreMain'] = Module.addOnPreMain = addOnPreMain;
00788 function addOnExit(cb) {
00789   __ATEXIT__.unshift(cb);
00790 }
00791 Module['addOnExit'] = Module.addOnExit = addOnExit;
00792 function addOnPostRun(cb) {
00793   __ATPOSTRUN__.unshift(cb);
00794 }
00795 Module['addOnPostRun'] = Module.addOnPostRun = addOnPostRun;
00796 // Tools
00797 // This processes a JS string into a C-line array of numbers, 0-terminated.
00798 // For LLVM-originating strings, see parser.js:parseLLVMString function
00799 function intArrayFromString(stringy, dontAddNull, length /* optional */) {
00800   var ret = (new Runtime.UTF8Processor()).processJSString(stringy);
00801   if (length) {
00802     ret.length = length;
00803   }
00804   if (!dontAddNull) {
00805     ret.push(0);
00806   }
00807   return ret;
00808 }
00809 Module['intArrayFromString'] = intArrayFromString;
00810 function intArrayToString(array) {
00811   var ret = [];
00812   for (var i = 0; i < array.length; i++) {
00813     var chr = array[i];
00814     if (chr > 0xFF) {
00815       chr &= 0xFF;
00816     }
00817     ret.push(String.fromCharCode(chr));
00818   }
00819   return ret.join('');
00820 }
00821 Module['intArrayToString'] = intArrayToString;
00822 // Write a Javascript array to somewhere in the heap
00823 function writeStringToMemory(string, buffer, dontAddNull) {
00824   var array = intArrayFromString(string, dontAddNull);
00825   var i = 0;
00826   while (i < array.length) {
00827     var chr = array[i];
00828     HEAP8[(((buffer)+(i))|0)]=chr
00829     i = i + 1;
00830   }
00831 }
00832 Module['writeStringToMemory'] = writeStringToMemory;
00833 function writeArrayToMemory(array, buffer) {
00834   for (var i = 0; i < array.length; i++) {
00835     HEAP8[(((buffer)+(i))|0)]=array[i];
00836   }
00837 }
00838 Module['writeArrayToMemory'] = writeArrayToMemory;
00839 function unSign(value, bits, ignore, sig) {
00840   if (value >= 0) {
00841     return value;
00842   }
00843   return bits <= 32 ? 2*Math.abs(1 << (bits-1)) + value // Need some trickery, since if bits == 32, we are right at the limit of the bits JS uses in bitshifts
00844                     : Math.pow(2, bits)         + value;
00845 }
00846 function reSign(value, bits, ignore, sig) {
00847   if (value <= 0) {
00848     return value;
00849   }
00850   var half = bits <= 32 ? Math.abs(1 << (bits-1)) // abs is needed if bits == 32
00851                         : Math.pow(2, bits-1);
00852   if (value >= half && (bits <= 32 || value > half)) { // for huge values, we can hit the precision limit and always get true here. so don't do that
00853                                                        // but, in general there is no perfect solution here. With 64-bit ints, we get rounding and errors
00854                                                        // TODO: In i64 mode 1, resign the two parts separately and safely
00855     value = -2*half + value; // Cannot bitshift half, as it may be at the limit of the bits JS uses in bitshifts
00856   }
00857   return value;
00858 }
00859 if (!Math['imul']) Math['imul'] = function(a, b) {
00860   var ah  = a >>> 16;
00861   var al = a & 0xffff;
00862   var bh  = b >>> 16;
00863   var bl = b & 0xffff;
00864   return (al*bl + ((ah*bl + al*bh) << 16))|0;
00865 };
00866 Math.imul = Math['imul'];
00867 // A counter of dependencies for calling run(). If we need to
00868 // do asynchronous work before running, increment this and
00869 // decrement it. Incrementing must happen in a place like
00870 // PRE_RUN_ADDITIONS (used by emcc to add file preloading).
00871 // Note that you can add dependencies in preRun, even though
00872 // it happens right before run - run will be postponed until
00873 // the dependencies are met.
00874 var runDependencies = 0;
00875 var runDependencyTracking = {};
00876 var calledInit = false, calledRun = false;
00877 var runDependencyWatcher = null;
00878 function addRunDependency(id) {
00879   runDependencies++;
00880   if (Module['monitorRunDependencies']) {
00881     Module['monitorRunDependencies'](runDependencies);
00882   }
00883   if (id) {
00884     assert(!runDependencyTracking[id]);
00885     runDependencyTracking[id] = 1;
00886   } else {
00887     Module.printErr('warning: run dependency added without ID');
00888   }
00889 }
00890 Module['addRunDependency'] = addRunDependency;
00891 function removeRunDependency(id) {
00892   runDependencies--;
00893   if (Module['monitorRunDependencies']) {
00894     Module['monitorRunDependencies'](runDependencies);
00895   }
00896   if (id) {
00897     assert(runDependencyTracking[id]);
00898     delete runDependencyTracking[id];
00899   } else {
00900     Module.printErr('warning: run dependency removed without ID');
00901   }
00902   if (runDependencies == 0) {
00903     if (runDependencyWatcher !== null) {
00904       clearInterval(runDependencyWatcher);
00905       runDependencyWatcher = null;
00906     }
00907     // If run has never been called, and we should call run (INVOKE_RUN is true, and Module.noInitialRun is not false)
00908     if (!calledRun && shouldRunNow) run();
00909   }
00910 }
00911 Module['removeRunDependency'] = removeRunDependency;
00912 Module["preloadedImages"] = {}; // maps url to image data
00913 Module["preloadedAudios"] = {}; // maps url to audio data
00914 function loadMemoryInitializer(filename) {
00915   function applyData(data) {
00916     HEAPU8.set(data, STATIC_BASE);
00917   }
00918   // always do this asynchronously, to keep shell and web as similar as possible
00919   addOnPreRun(function() {
00920     if (ENVIRONMENT_IS_NODE || ENVIRONMENT_IS_SHELL) {
00921       applyData(Module['readBinary'](filename));
00922     } else {
00923       Browser.asyncLoad(filename, function(data) {
00924         applyData(data);
00925       }, function(data) {
00926         throw 'could not load memory initializer ' + filename;
00927       });
00928     }
00929   });
00930 }

01262         if (typeof XMLHttpRequest !== 'undefined') {
01263           if (!ENVIRONMENT_IS_WORKER) throw 'Cannot do synchronous binary XHRs outside webworkers in modern browsers. Use --embed-file or --preload-file in emcc';
01264           // Lazy chunked Uint8Array (implements get and length from Uint8Array). Actual getting is abstracted away for eventual reuse.
01265           var LazyUint8Array = function() {
01266             this.lengthKnown = false;
01267             this.chunks = []; // Loaded chunks. Index is the chunk number
01268           }
01269           LazyUint8Array.prototype.get = function(idx) {
01270             if (idx > this.length-1 || idx < 0) {
01271               return undefined;
01272             }
01273             var chunkOffset = idx % this.chunkSize;
01274             var chunkNum = Math.floor(idx / this.chunkSize);
01275             return this.getter(chunkNum)[chunkOffset];
01276           }
01277           LazyUint8Array.prototype.setDataGetter = function(getter) {
01278             this.getter = getter;
01279           }
01280           LazyUint8Array.prototype.cacheLength = function() {
01281               // Find length
01282               var xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
01283               xhr.open('HEAD', url, false);
01284               xhr.send(null);
01285               if (!(xhr.status >= 200 && xhr.status < 300 || xhr.status === 304)) throw new Error("Couldn't load " + url + ". Status: " + xhr.status);
01286               var datalength = Number(xhr.getResponseHeader("Content-length"));
01287               var header;
01288               var hasByteServing = (header = xhr.getResponseHeader("Accept-Ranges")) && header === "bytes";
01289               var chunkSize = 1024*1024; // Chunk size in bytes
01290               if (!hasByteServing) chunkSize = datalength;
01291               // Function to get a range from the remote URL.
01292               var doXHR = (function(from, to) {
01293                 if (from > to) throw new Error("invalid range (" + from + ", " + to + ") or no bytes requested!");
01294                 if (to > datalength-1) throw new Error("only " + datalength + " bytes available! programmer error!");
01295                 // TODO: Use mozResponseArrayBuffer, responseStream, etc. if available.
01296                 var xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
01297                 xhr.open('GET', url, false);
01298                 if (datalength !== chunkSize) xhr.setRequestHeader("Range", "bytes=" + from + "-" + to);
01299                 // Some hints to the browser that we want binary data.
01300                 if (typeof Uint8Array != 'undefined') xhr.responseType = 'arraybuffer';
01301                 if (xhr.overrideMimeType) {
01302                   xhr.overrideMimeType('text/plain; charset=x-user-defined');
01303                 }
01304                 xhr.send(null);
01305                 if (!(xhr.status >= 200 && xhr.status < 300 || xhr.status === 304)) throw new Error("Couldn't load " + url + ". Status: " + xhr.status);
01306                 if (xhr.response !== undefined) {
01307                   return new Uint8Array(xhr.response || []);
01308                 } else {
01309                   return intArrayFromString(xhr.responseText || '', true);
01310                 }
01311               });
01312               var lazyArray = this;
01313               lazyArray.setDataGetter(function(chunkNum) {
01314                 var start = chunkNum * chunkSize;
01315                 var end = (chunkNum+1) * chunkSize - 1; // including this byte
01316                 end = Math.min(end, datalength-1); // if datalength-1 is selected, this is the last block
01317                 if (typeof(lazyArray.chunks[chunkNum]) === "undefined") {
01318                   lazyArray.chunks[chunkNum] = doXHR(start, end);
01319                 }
01320                 if (typeof(lazyArray.chunks[chunkNum]) === "undefined") throw new Error("doXHR failed!");
01321                 return lazyArray.chunks[chunkNum];
01322               });
01323               this._length = datalength;
01324               this._chunkSize = chunkSize;
01325               this.lengthKnown = true;
01326           }
01327           var lazyArray = new LazyUint8Array();
01328           Object.defineProperty(lazyArray, "length", {
01329               get: function() {
01330                   if(!this.lengthKnown) {
01331                       this.cacheLength();
01332                   }
01333                   return this._length;
01334               }
01335           });
01336           Object.defineProperty(lazyArray, "chunkSize", {
01337               get: function() {
01338                   if(!this.lengthKnown) {
01339                       this.cacheLength();
01340                   }
01341                   return this._chunkSize;
01342               }
01343           });
01344           var properties = { isDevice: false, contents: lazyArray };
01345         } else {
01346           var properties = { isDevice: false, url: url };
01347         }
01348         return FS.createFile(parent, name, properties, canRead, canWrite);

01537           'void*', ALLOC_NORMAL) ], 'void*', ALLOC_NONE, __impure_ptr);

01554   var ___dirent_struct_layout={__size__:1040,d_ino:0,d_name:4,d_off:1028,d_reclen:1032,d_type:1036};function _open(path, oflag, varargs) {
01555       // int open(const char *path, int oflag, ...);
01556       // http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/009695399/functions/open.html
01557       // NOTE: This implementation tries to mimic glibc rather than strictly
01558       // following the POSIX standard.
01559       var mode = HEAP32[((varargs)>>2)];
01560       // Simplify flags.
01561       var accessMode = oflag & 3;
01562       var isWrite = accessMode != 0;
01563       var isRead = accessMode != 1;
01564       var isCreate = Boolean(oflag & 512);
01565       var isExistCheck = Boolean(oflag & 2048);
01566       var isTruncate = Boolean(oflag & 1024);
01567       var isAppend = Boolean(oflag & 8);
01568       // Verify path.
01569       var origPath = path;
01570       path = FS.analyzePath(Pointer_stringify(path));
01571       if (!path.parentExists) {
01572         ___setErrNo(path.error);
01573         return -1;
01574       }
01575       var target = path.object || null;
01576       var finalPath;
01577       // Verify the file exists, create if needed and allowed.
01578       if (target) {
01579         if (isCreate && isExistCheck) {
01580           ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EEXIST);
01581           return -1;
01582         }
01583         if ((isWrite || isTruncate) && target.isFolder) {
01584           ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EISDIR);
01585           return -1;
01586         }
01587         if (isRead && !target.read || isWrite && !target.write) {
01588           ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EACCES);
01589           return -1;
01590         }
01591         if (isTruncate && !target.isDevice) {
01592           target.contents = [];
01593         } else {
01594           if (!FS.forceLoadFile(target)) {
01595             ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EIO);
01596             return -1;
01597           }
01598         }
01599         finalPath = path.path;
01600       } else {
01601         if (!isCreate) {
01602           ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.ENOENT);
01603           return -1;
01604         }
01605         if (!path.parentObject.write) {
01606           ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EACCES);
01607           return -1;
01608         }
01609         target = FS.createDataFile(path.parentObject, path.name, [],
01610                                    mode & 0x100, mode & 0x80);  // S_IRUSR, S_IWUSR.
01611         finalPath = path.parentPath + '/' + path.name;
01612       }
01613       // Actually create an open stream.
01614       var id;
01615       if (target.isFolder) {
01616         var entryBuffer = 0;
01617         if (___dirent_struct_layout) {
01618           entryBuffer = _malloc(___dirent_struct_layout.__size__);
01619         }
01620         var contents = [];
01621         for (var key in target.contents) contents.push(key);
01622         id = FS.createFileHandle({
01623           path: finalPath,
01624           object: target,
01625           // An index into contents. Special values: -2 is ".", -1 is "..".
01626           position: -2,
01627           isRead: true,
01628           isWrite: false,
01629           isAppend: false,
01630           error: false,
01631           eof: false,
01632           ungotten: [],
01633           // Folder-specific properties:
01634           // Remember the contents at the time of opening in an array, so we can
01635           // seek between them relying on a single order.
01636           contents: contents,
01637           // Each stream has its own area for readdir() returns.
01638           currentEntry: entryBuffer
01639         });
01640       } else {
01641         id = FS.createFileHandle({
01642           path: finalPath,
01643           object: target,
01644           position: 0,
01645           isRead: isRead,
01646           isWrite: isWrite,
01647           isAppend: isAppend,
01648           error: false,
01649           eof: false,
01650           ungotten: []
01651         });
01652       }
01653       return id;
01654     }function _fopen(filename, mode) {
01655       // FILE *fopen(const char *restrict filename, const char *restrict mode);
01656       // http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/000095399/functions/fopen.html
01657       var flags;
01658       mode = Pointer_stringify(mode);
01659       if (mode[0] == 'r') {
01660         if (mode.indexOf('+') != -1) {
01661           flags = 2;
01662         } else {
01663           flags = 0;
01664         }
01665       } else if (mode[0] == 'w') {
01666         if (mode.indexOf('+') != -1) {
01667           flags = 2;
01668         } else {
01669           flags = 1;
01670         }
01671         flags |= 512;
01672         flags |= 1024;
01673       } else if (mode[0] == 'a') {
01674         if (mode.indexOf('+') != -1) {
01675           flags = 2;
01676         } else {
01677           flags = 1;
01678         }
01679         flags |= 512;
01680         flags |= 8;
01681       } else {
01682         ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EINVAL);
01683         return 0;
01684       }
01685       var ret = _open(filename, flags, allocate([0x1FF, 0, 0, 0], 'i32', ALLOC_STACK));  // All creation permissions.
01686       return (ret == -1) ? 0 : ret;
01687     }
01688   function _recv(fd, buf, len, flags) {
01689       var info = FS.streams[fd];
01690       if (!info) return -1;
01691       if (!info.hasData()) {
01692         ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EAGAIN); // no data, and all sockets are nonblocking, so this is the right behavior
01693         return -1;
01694       }
01695       var buffer = info.inQueue.shift();
01696       if (len < buffer.length) {
01697         if (info.stream) {
01698           // This is tcp (reliable), so if not all was read, keep it
01699           info.inQueue.unshift(buffer.subarray(len));
01700         }
01701         buffer = buffer.subarray(0, len);
01702       }
01703       HEAPU8.set(buffer, buf);
01704       return buffer.length;
01705     }
01706   function _pread(fildes, buf, nbyte, offset) {
01707       // ssize_t pread(int fildes, void *buf, size_t nbyte, off_t offset);
01708       // http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/000095399/functions/read.html
01709       var stream = FS.streams[fildes];
01710       if (!stream || stream.object.isDevice) {
01711         ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EBADF);
01712         return -1;
01713       } else if (!stream.isRead) {
01714         ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EACCES);
01715         return -1;
01716       } else if (stream.object.isFolder) {
01717         ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EISDIR);
01718         return -1;
01719       } else if (nbyte < 0 || offset < 0) {
01720         ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EINVAL);
01721         return -1;
01722       } else if (offset >= stream.object.contents.length) {
01723         return 0;
01724       } else {
01725         var bytesRead = 0;
01726         var contents = stream.object.contents;
01727         var size = Math.min(contents.length - offset, nbyte);
01728         assert(size >= 0);
01729         if (contents.subarray) { // typed array
01730           HEAPU8.set(contents.subarray(offset, offset+size), buf);
01731         } else
01732         if (contents.slice) { // normal array
01733           for (var i = 0; i < size; i++) {
01734             HEAP8[(((buf)+(i))|0)]=contents[offset + i]
01735           }
01736         } else {
01737           for (var i = 0; i < size; i++) { // LazyUint8Array from sync binary XHR
01738             HEAP8[(((buf)+(i))|0)]=contents.get(offset + i)
01739           }
01740         }
01741         bytesRead += size;
01742         return bytesRead;
01743       }
01744     }function _read(fildes, buf, nbyte) {
01745       // ssize_t read(int fildes, void *buf, size_t nbyte);
01746       // http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/000095399/functions/read.html
01747       var stream = FS.streams[fildes];
01748       if (stream && ('socket' in stream)) {
01749         return _recv(fildes, buf, nbyte, 0);
01750       } else if (!stream) {
01751         ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EBADF);
01752         return -1;
01753       } else if (!stream.isRead) {
01754         ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EACCES);
01755         return -1;
01756       } else if (nbyte < 0) {
01757         ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EINVAL);
01758         return -1;
01759       } else {
01760         var bytesRead;
01761         if (stream.object.isDevice) {
01762           if (stream.object.input) {
01763             bytesRead = 0;
01764             for (var i = 0; i < nbyte; i++) {
01765               try {
01766                 var result = stream.object.input();
01767               } catch (e) {
01768                 ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EIO);
01769                 return -1;
01770               }
01771               if (result === undefined && bytesRead === 0) {
01772                 ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EAGAIN);
01773                 return -1;
01774               }
01775               if (result === null || result === undefined) break;
01776               bytesRead++;
01777               HEAP8[(((buf)+(i))|0)]=result
01778             }
01779             return bytesRead;
01780           } else {
01781             ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.ENXIO);
01782             return -1;
01783           }
01784         } else {
01785           bytesRead = _pread(fildes, buf, nbyte, stream.position);
01786           assert(bytesRead >= -1);
01787           if (bytesRead != -1) {
01788             stream.position += bytesRead;
01789           }
01790           return bytesRead;
01791         }
01792       }
01793     }function _fread(ptr, size, nitems, stream) {
01794       // size_t fread(void *restrict ptr, size_t size, size_t nitems, FILE *restrict stream);
01795       // http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/000095399/functions/fread.html
01796       var bytesToRead = nitems * size;
01797       if (bytesToRead == 0) {
01798         return 0;
01799       }
01800       var bytesRead = 0;
01801       var streamObj = FS.streams[stream];
01802       while (streamObj.ungotten.length && bytesToRead > 0) {
01803         HEAP8[((ptr++)|0)]=streamObj.ungotten.pop()
01804         bytesToRead--;
01805         bytesRead++;
01806       }
01807       var err = _read(stream, ptr, bytesToRead);
01808       if (err == -1) {
01809         if (streamObj) streamObj.error = true;
01810         return 0;
01811       }
01812       bytesRead += err;
01813       if (bytesRead < bytesToRead) streamObj.eof = true;
01814       return Math.floor(bytesRead / size);
01815     }
01816   function _close(fildes) {
01817       // int close(int fildes);
01818       // http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/000095399/functions/close.html
01819       if (FS.streams[fildes]) {

01822         }

01824         return 0;
01825       } else {
01826         ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EBADF);
01827         return -1;
01828       }
01829     }

01846   function _lseek(fildes, offset, whence) {
01847       // off_t lseek(int fildes, off_t offset, int whence);
01848       // http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/000095399/functions/lseek.html
01849       if (FS.streams[fildes] && !FS.streams[fildes].object.isDevice) {

01851         var position = offset;
01852         if (whence === 1) {  // SEEK_CUR.
01853           position += stream.position;
01854         } else if (whence === 2) {  // SEEK_END.

01863           return position;
01864         }
01865       } else {
01866         ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EBADF);
01867         return -1;
01868       }

01873       if (ret == -1) {

01875       } else {

01910   function _send(fd, buf, len, flags) {

01916   function _pwrite(fildes, buf, nbyte, offset) {
01917       // ssize_t pwrite(int fildes, const void *buf, size_t nbyte, off_t offset);
01918       // http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/000095399/functions/write.html
01919       var stream = FS.streams[fildes];
01920       if (!stream || stream.object.isDevice) {
01921         ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EBADF);
01922         return -1;
01923       } else if (!stream.isWrite) {
01924         ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EACCES);
01925         return -1;
01926       } else if (stream.object.isFolder) {
01927         ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EISDIR);
01928         return -1;
01929       } else if (nbyte < 0 || offset < 0) {
01930         ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EINVAL);
01931         return -1;
01932       } else {
01933         var contents = stream.object.contents;
01934         while (contents.length < offset) contents.push(0);
01935         for (var i = 0; i < nbyte; i++) {
01936           contents[offset + i] = HEAPU8[(((buf)+(i))|0)];
01937         }
01938         stream.object.timestamp = Date.now();
01939         return i;
01940       }
01941     }function _write(fildes, buf, nbyte) {
01942       // ssize_t write(int fildes, const void *buf, size_t nbyte);
01943       // http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/000095399/functions/write.html
01944       var stream = FS.streams[fildes];
01945       if (stream && ('socket' in stream)) {
01946           return _send(fildes, buf, nbyte, 0);
01947       } else if (!stream) {
01948         ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EBADF);
01949         return -1;
01950       } else if (!stream.isWrite) {
01951         ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EACCES);
01952         return -1;
01953       } else if (nbyte < 0) {
01954         ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EINVAL);
01955         return -1;
01956       } else {
01957         if (stream.object.isDevice) {
01958           if (stream.object.output) {
01959             for (var i = 0; i < nbyte; i++) {
01960               try {
01961                 stream.object.output(HEAP8[(((buf)+(i))|0)]);
01962               } catch (e) {
01963                 ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EIO);
01964                 return -1;
01965               }
01966             }
01967             stream.object.timestamp = Date.now();
01968             return i;
01969           } else {
01970             ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.ENXIO);
01971             return -1;
01972           }
01973         } else {
01974           var bytesWritten = _pwrite(fildes, buf, nbyte, stream.position);
01975           if (bytesWritten != -1) stream.position += bytesWritten;
01976           return bytesWritten;
01977         }
01978       }
01979     }function _fwrite(ptr, size, nitems, stream) {
01980       // size_t fwrite(const void *restrict ptr, size_t size, size_t nitems, FILE *restrict stream);
01981       // http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/000095399/functions/fwrite.html
01982       var bytesToWrite = nitems * size;
01983       if (bytesToWrite == 0) return 0;
01984       var bytesWritten = _write(stream, ptr, bytesToWrite);
01985       if (bytesWritten == -1) {
01986         if (FS.streams[stream]) FS.streams[stream].error = true;
01987         return 0;
01988       } else {
01989         return Math.floor(bytesWritten / size);
01990       }
01991     }
01992   function __reallyNegative(x) {
01993       return x < 0 || (x === 0 && (1/x) === -Infinity);
01994     }function __formatString(format, varargs) {
01995       var textIndex = format;
01996       var argIndex = 0;
01997       function getNextArg(type) {
01998         // NOTE: Explicitly ignoring type safety. Otherwise this fails:
01999         //       int x = 4; printf("%c\n", (char)x);
02000         var ret;
02001         if (type === 'double') {
02002           ret = HEAPF64[(((varargs)+(argIndex))>>3)];
02003         } else if (type == 'i64') {
02004           ret = [HEAP32[(((varargs)+(argIndex))>>2)],
02005                  HEAP32[(((varargs)+(argIndex+8))>>2)]];
02006           argIndex += 8; // each 32-bit chunk is in a 64-bit block
02007         } else {
02008           type = 'i32'; // varargs are always i32, i64, or double
02009           ret = HEAP32[(((varargs)+(argIndex))>>2)];
02010         }
02011         argIndex += Math.max(Runtime.getNativeFieldSize(type), Runtime.getAlignSize(type, null, true));
02012         return ret;
02013       }
02014       var ret = [];
02015       var curr, next, currArg;
02016       while(1) {
02017         var startTextIndex = textIndex;
02018         curr = HEAP8[(textIndex)];
02019         if (curr === 0) break;
02020         next = HEAP8[((textIndex+1)|0)];
02021         if (curr == 37) {
02022           // Handle flags.
02023           var flagAlwaysSigned = false;
02024           var flagLeftAlign = false;
02025           var flagAlternative = false;
02026           var flagZeroPad = false;
02027           flagsLoop: while (1) {
02028             switch (next) {
02029               case 43:
02030                 flagAlwaysSigned = true;
02031                 break;
02032               case 45:
02033                 flagLeftAlign = true;
02034                 break;
02035               case 35:
02036                 flagAlternative = true;
02037                 break;
02038               case 48:
02039                 if (flagZeroPad) {
02040                   break flagsLoop;
02041                 } else {
02042                   flagZeroPad = true;
02043                   break;
02044                 }
02045               default:
02046                 break flagsLoop;
02047             }
02048             textIndex++;
02049             next = HEAP8[((textIndex+1)|0)];
02050           }
02051           // Handle width.
02052           var width = 0;
02053           if (next == 42) {
02054             width = getNextArg('i32');
02055             textIndex++;
02056             next = HEAP8[((textIndex+1)|0)];
02057           } else {
02058             while (next >= 48 && next <= 57) {
02059               width = width * 10 + (next - 48);
02060               textIndex++;
02061               next = HEAP8[((textIndex+1)|0)];
02062             }
02063           }
02064           // Handle precision.
02065           var precisionSet = false;
02066           if (next == 46) {
02067             var precision = 0;
02068             precisionSet = true;
02069             textIndex++;
02070             next = HEAP8[((textIndex+1)|0)];
02071             if (next == 42) {
02072               precision = getNextArg('i32');
02073               textIndex++;
02074             } else {
02075               while(1) {
02076                 var precisionChr = HEAP8[((textIndex+1)|0)];
02077                 if (precisionChr < 48 ||
02078                     precisionChr > 57) break;
02079                 precision = precision * 10 + (precisionChr - 48);
02080                 textIndex++;
02081               }
02082             }
02083             next = HEAP8[((textIndex+1)|0)];
02084           } else {
02085             var precision = 6; // Standard default.
02086           }
02087           // Handle integer sizes. WARNING: These assume a 32-bit architecture!
02088           var argSize;
02089           switch (String.fromCharCode(next)) {
02090             case 'h':
02091               var nextNext = HEAP8[((textIndex+2)|0)];
02092               if (nextNext == 104) {
02093                 textIndex++;
02094                 argSize = 1; // char (actually i32 in varargs)
02095               } else {
02096                 argSize = 2; // short (actually i32 in varargs)
02097               }
02098               break;
02099             case 'l':
02100               var nextNext = HEAP8[((textIndex+2)|0)];
02101               if (nextNext == 108) {
02102                 textIndex++;
02103                 argSize = 8; // long long
02104               } else {
02105                 argSize = 4; // long
02106               }
02107               break;
02108             case 'L': // long long
02109             case 'q': // int64_t
02110             case 'j': // intmax_t
02111               argSize = 8;
02112               break;
02113             case 'z': // size_t
02114             case 't': // ptrdiff_t
02115             case 'I': // signed ptrdiff_t or unsigned size_t
02116               argSize = 4;
02117               break;
02118             default:
02119               argSize = null;
02120           }
02121           if (argSize) textIndex++;
02122           next = HEAP8[((textIndex+1)|0)];
02123           // Handle type specifier.
02124           switch (String.fromCharCode(next)) {
02125             case 'd': case 'i': case 'u': case 'o': case 'x': case 'X': case 'p': {
02126               // Integer.
02127               var signed = next == 100 || next == 105;
02128               argSize = argSize || 4;
02129               var currArg = getNextArg('i' + (argSize * 8));
02130               var origArg = currArg;
02131               var argText;
02132               // Flatten i64-1 [low, high] into a (slightly rounded) double
02133               if (argSize == 8) {
02134                 currArg = Runtime.makeBigInt(currArg[0], currArg[1], next == 117);
02135               }
02136               // Truncate to requested size.
02137               if (argSize <= 4) {
02138                 var limit = Math.pow(256, argSize) - 1;
02139                 currArg = (signed ? reSign : unSign)(currArg & limit, argSize * 8);
02140               }
02141               // Format the number.
02142               var currAbsArg = Math.abs(currArg);
02143               var prefix = '';
02144               if (next == 100 || next == 105) {
02145                 if (argSize == 8 && i64Math) argText = i64Math.stringify(origArg[0], origArg[1], null); else
02146                 argText = reSign(currArg, 8 * argSize, 1).toString(10);
02147               } else if (next == 117) {
02148                 if (argSize == 8 && i64Math) argText = i64Math.stringify(origArg[0], origArg[1], true); else
02149                 argText = unSign(currArg, 8 * argSize, 1).toString(10);
02150                 currArg = Math.abs(currArg);
02151               } else if (next == 111) {
02152                 argText = (flagAlternative ? '0' : '') + currAbsArg.toString(8);
02153               } else if (next == 120 || next == 88) {
02154                 prefix = (flagAlternative && currArg != 0) ? '0x' : '';
02155                 if (argSize == 8 && i64Math) {
02156                   if (origArg[1]) {
02157                     argText = (origArg[1]>>>0).toString(16);
02158                     var lower = (origArg[0]>>>0).toString(16);
02159                     while (lower.length < 8) lower = '0' + lower;
02160                     argText += lower;
02161                   } else {
02162                     argText = (origArg[0]>>>0).toString(16);
02163                   }
02164                 } else
02165                 if (currArg < 0) {
02166                   // Represent negative numbers in hex as 2's complement.
02167                   currArg = -currArg;
02168                   argText = (currAbsArg - 1).toString(16);
02169                   var buffer = [];
02170                   for (var i = 0; i < argText.length; i++) {
02171                     buffer.push((0xF - parseInt(argText[i], 16)).toString(16));
02172                   }
02173                   argText = buffer.join('');
02174                   while (argText.length < argSize * 2) argText = 'f' + argText;
02175                 } else {
02176                   argText = currAbsArg.toString(16);
02177                 }
02178                 if (next == 88) {
02179                   prefix = prefix.toUpperCase();
02180                   argText = argText.toUpperCase();
02181                 }
02182               } else if (next == 112) {
02183                 if (currAbsArg === 0) {
02184                   argText = '(nil)';
02185                 } else {
02186                   prefix = '0x';
02187                   argText = currAbsArg.toString(16);
02188                 }
02189               }
02190               if (precisionSet) {
02191                 while (argText.length < precision) {
02192                   argText = '0' + argText;
02193                 }
02194               }
02195               // Add sign if needed
02196               if (flagAlwaysSigned) {
02197                 if (currArg < 0) {
02198                   prefix = '-' + prefix;
02199                 } else {
02200                   prefix = '+' + prefix;
02201                 }
02202               }
02203               // Add padding.
02204               while (prefix.length + argText.length < width) {
02205                 if (flagLeftAlign) {
02206                   argText += ' ';
02207                 } else {
02208                   if (flagZeroPad) {
02209                     argText = '0' + argText;
02210                   } else {
02211                     prefix = ' ' + prefix;
02212                   }
02213                 }
02214               }
02215               // Insert the result into the buffer.
02216               argText = prefix + argText;
02217               argText.split('').forEach(function(chr) {
02218                 ret.push(chr.charCodeAt(0));
02219               });
02220               break;
02221             }
02222             case 'f': case 'F': case 'e': case 'E': case 'g': case 'G': {
02223               // Float.
02224               var currArg = getNextArg('double');
02225               var argText;
02226               if (isNaN(currArg)) {
02227                 argText = 'nan';
02228                 flagZeroPad = false;
02229               } else if (!isFinite(currArg)) {
02230                 argText = (currArg < 0 ? '-' : '') + 'inf';
02231                 flagZeroPad = false;
02232               } else {
02233                 var isGeneral = false;
02234                 var effectivePrecision = Math.min(precision, 20);
02235                 // Convert g/G to f/F or e/E, as per:
02236                 // http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/9699919799/functions/printf.html
02237                 if (next == 103 || next == 71) {
02238                   isGeneral = true;
02239                   precision = precision || 1;
02240                   var exponent = parseInt(currArg.toExponential(effectivePrecision).split('e')[1], 10);
02241                   if (precision > exponent && exponent >= -4) {
02242                     next = ((next == 103) ? 'f' : 'F').charCodeAt(0);
02243                     precision -= exponent + 1;
02244                   } else {
02245                     next = ((next == 103) ? 'e' : 'E').charCodeAt(0);
02246                     precision--;
02247                   }
02248                   effectivePrecision = Math.min(precision, 20);
02249                 }
02250                 if (next == 101 || next == 69) {
02251                   argText = currArg.toExponential(effectivePrecision);
02252                   // Make sure the exponent has at least 2 digits.
02253                   if (/[eE][-+]\d$/.test(argText)) {
02254                     argText = argText.slice(0, -1) + '0' + argText.slice(-1);
02255                   }
02256                 } else if (next == 102 || next == 70) {
02257                   argText = currArg.toFixed(effectivePrecision);
02258                   if (currArg === 0 && __reallyNegative(currArg)) {
02259                     argText = '-' + argText;
02260                   }
02261                 }
02262                 var parts = argText.split('e');
02263                 if (isGeneral && !flagAlternative) {
02264                   // Discard trailing zeros and periods.
02265                   while (parts[0].length > 1 && parts[0].indexOf('.') != -1 &&
02266                          (parts[0].slice(-1) == '0' || parts[0].slice(-1) == '.')) {
02267                     parts[0] = parts[0].slice(0, -1);
02268                   }
02269                 } else {
02270                   // Make sure we have a period in alternative mode.
02271                   if (flagAlternative && argText.indexOf('.') == -1) parts[0] += '.';
02272                   // Zero pad until required precision.
02273                   while (precision > effectivePrecision++) parts[0] += '0';
02274                 }
02275                 argText = parts[0] + (parts.length > 1 ? 'e' + parts[1] : '');
02276                 // Capitalize 'E' if needed.
02277                 if (next == 69) argText = argText.toUpperCase();
02278                 // Add sign.
02279                 if (flagAlwaysSigned && currArg >= 0) {
02280                   argText = '+' + argText;
02281                 }
02282               }
02283               // Add padding.
02284               while (argText.length < width) {
02285                 if (flagLeftAlign) {
02286                   argText += ' ';
02287                 } else {
02288                   if (flagZeroPad && (argText[0] == '-' || argText[0] == '+')) {
02289                     argText = argText[0] + '0' + argText.slice(1);
02290                   } else {
02291                     argText = (flagZeroPad ? '0' : ' ') + argText;
02292                   }
02293                 }
02294               }
02295               // Adjust case.
02296               if (next < 97) argText = argText.toUpperCase();
02297               // Insert the result into the buffer.
02298               argText.split('').forEach(function(chr) {
02299                 ret.push(chr.charCodeAt(0));
02300               });
02301               break;
02302             }
02303             case 's': {
02304               // String.
02305               var arg = getNextArg('i8*');
02306               var argLength = arg ? _strlen(arg) : '(null)'.length;
02307               if (precisionSet) argLength = Math.min(argLength, precision);
02308               if (!flagLeftAlign) {
02309                 while (argLength < width--) {
02310                   ret.push(32);
02311                 }
02312               }
02313               if (arg) {
02314                 for (var i = 0; i < argLength; i++) {
02315                   ret.push(HEAPU8[((arg++)|0)]);
02316                 }
02317               } else {
02318                 ret = ret.concat(intArrayFromString('(null)'.substr(0, argLength), true));
02319               }
02320               if (flagLeftAlign) {
02321                 while (argLength < width--) {
02322                   ret.push(32);
02323                 }
02324               }
02325               break;
02326             }
02327             case 'c': {
02328               // Character.
02329               if (flagLeftAlign) ret.push(getNextArg('i8'));
02330               while (--width > 0) {
02331                 ret.push(32);
02332               }
02333               if (!flagLeftAlign) ret.push(getNextArg('i8'));
02334               break;
02335             }
02336             case 'n': {
02337               // Write the length written so far to the next parameter.
02338               var ptr = getNextArg('i32*');
02339               HEAP32[((ptr)>>2)]=ret.length
02340               break;
02341             }
02342             case '%': {
02343               // Literal percent sign.
02344               ret.push(curr);
02345               break;
02346             }
02347             default: {
02348               // Unknown specifiers remain untouched.
02349               for (var i = startTextIndex; i < textIndex + 2; i++) {
02350                 ret.push(HEAP8[(i)]);
02351               }
02352             }
02353           }
02354           textIndex += 2;
02355           // TODO: Support a/A (hex float) and m (last error) specifiers.
02356           // TODO: Support %1${specifier} for arg selection.
02357         } else {
02358           ret.push(curr);
02359           textIndex += 1;
02360         }
02361       }
02362       return ret;
02363     }function _fprintf(stream, format, varargs) {
02364       // int fprintf(FILE *restrict stream, const char *restrict format, ...);
02365       // http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/000095399/functions/printf.html
02366       var result = __formatString(format, varargs);
02367       var stack = Runtime.stackSave();
02368       var ret = _fwrite(allocate(result, 'i8', ALLOC_STACK), 1, result.length, stream);
02369       Runtime.stackRestore(stack);
02370       return ret;
02371     }function _printf(format, varargs) {
02372       // int printf(const char *restrict format, ...);
02373       // http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/000095399/functions/printf.html
02374       var stdout = HEAP32[((_stdout)>>2)];
02375       return _fprintf(stdout, format, varargs);

02378   function _fputs(s, stream) {

02383   function _fputc(c, stream) {
02384       // int fputc(int c, FILE *stream);
02385       // http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/000095399/functions/fputc.html
02386       var chr = unSign(c & 0xFF);
02387       HEAP8[((_fputc.ret)|0)]=chr

02389       if (ret == -1) {

02391         return -1;
02392       } else {

02394       }
02395     }function _puts(s) {
02396       // int puts(const char *s);
02397       // http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/000095399/functions/puts.html

02440   function _qsort2(base, num, size, cmp) {
02441       // forward calls to the JavaScript sort method
02442       // first, sort the items logically
02443       var keys = [];
02444 
02445       for (var i = 0; i < num; i++) {
02446         keys.push(HEAP32[(base + i * size) >> 2]);
02447       }
02448 
02449       keys.sort(function(a, b) {
02450         return a - b;
02451       });
02452 
02453       // apply the sort
02454       for (var i = 0; i < num; i++) {
02455         HEAP32[(base+i*size >> 2)] = keys[i];
02456       }
02457     }
02458 
02459   function _qsort(base, num, size, cmp) {
02460       if (num == 0 || size == 0) return;
02461       // forward calls to the JavaScript sort method
02462       // first, sort the items logically
02463       var keys = [];
02464       for (var i = 0; i < num; i++) keys.push(i);
02465       keys.sort(function(a, b) {
02466         return Module['dynCall_iii'](cmp, base+a*size, base+b*size);
02467       });
02468       // apply the sort
02469       var temp = _malloc(num*size);
02470       _memcpy(temp, base, num*size);
02471       for (var i = 0; i < num; i++) {
02472         if (keys[i] == i) continue; // already in place
02473         _memcpy(base+i*size, temp+keys[i]*size, size);
02474       }
02475       _free(temp);
02476     }

02479   function _strncmp(px, py, n) {
02480       var i = 0;
02481       while (i < n) {
02482         var x = HEAPU8[(((px)+(i))|0)];
02483         var y = HEAPU8[(((py)+(i))|0)];
02484         if (x == y && x == 0) return 0;
02485         if (x == 0) return -1;
02486         if (y == 0) return 1;
02487         if (x == y) {
02488           i ++;
02489           continue;
02490         } else {
02491           return x > y ? 1 : -1;
02492         }
02493       }
02494       return 0;
02495     }function _strcmp(px, py) {
02496       return _strncmp(px, py, TOTAL_MEMORY);
02497     }
02498   function _snprintf(s, n, format, varargs) {
02499       // int snprintf(char *restrict s, size_t n, const char *restrict format, ...);
02500       // http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/000095399/functions/printf.html
02501       var result = __formatString(format, varargs);
02502       var limit = (n === undefined) ? result.length
02503                                     : Math.min(result.length, Math.max(n - 1, 0));
02504       if (s < 0) {
02505         s = -s;
02506         var buf = _malloc(limit+1);
02507         HEAP32[((s)>>2)]=buf;
02508         s = buf;
02509       }
02510       for (var i = 0; i < limit; i++) {
02511         HEAP8[(((s)+(i))|0)]=result[i];
02512       }
02513       if (limit < n || (n === undefined)) HEAP8[(((s)+(i))|0)]=0;
02514       return result.length;
02515     }

02523   function _bsearch(key, base, num, size, compar) {
02524       var cmp = function(x, y) {
02525         return Module['dynCall_iii'](compar, x, y);
02526       };
02527       var left = 0;
02528       var right = num;
02529       var mid, test, addr;
02530       while (left < right) {
02531         mid = (left + right) >>> 1;
02532         addr = base + (mid * size);
02533         test = cmp(key, addr);
02534         if (test < 0) {
02535           right = mid;
02536         } else if (test > 0) {
02537           left = mid + 1;
02538         } else {
02539           return addr;
02540         }
02541       }
02542       return 0;
02543     }

02583   function _truncate(path, length) {
02584       // int truncate(const char *path, off_t length);
02585       // http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/000095399/functions/truncate.html
02586       // NOTE: The path argument may be a string, to simplify ftruncate().
02587       if (length < 0) {
02588         ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EINVAL);
02589         return -1;
02590       } else {
02591         if (typeof path !== 'string') path = Pointer_stringify(path);
02592         var target = FS.findObject(path);
02593         if (target === null) return -1;
02594         if (target.isFolder) {
02595           ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EISDIR);
02596           return -1;
02597         } else if (target.isDevice) {
02598           ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EINVAL);
02599           return -1;
02600         } else if (!target.write) {
02601           ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EACCES);
02602           return -1;
02603         } else {
02604           var contents = target.contents;
02605           if (length < contents.length) contents.length = length;
02606           else while (length > contents.length) contents.push(0);
02607           target.timestamp = Date.now();
02608           return 0;
02609         }
02610       }
02611     }function _ftruncate(fildes, length) {

02614       if (FS.streams[fildes] && FS.streams[fildes].isWrite) {
02615         return _truncate(FS.streams[fildes].path, length);
02616       } else if (FS.streams[fildes]) {
02617         ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EINVAL);
02618         return -1;
02619       } else {
02620         ___setErrNo(ERRNO_CODES.EBADF);
02621         return -1;
02622       }
02623     }

02777   function _sbrk(bytes) {
02778       // Implement a Linux-like 'memory area' for our 'process'.
02779       // Changes the size of the memory area by |bytes|; returns the
02780       // address of the previous top ('break') of the memory area
02781       // We control the "dynamic" memory - DYNAMIC_BASE to DYNAMICTOP
02782       var self = _sbrk;
02783       if (!self.called) {
02784         DYNAMICTOP = alignMemoryPage(DYNAMICTOP); // make sure we start out aligned
02785         self.called = true;
02786         assert(Runtime.dynamicAlloc);
02787         self.alloc = Runtime.dynamicAlloc;
02788         Runtime.dynamicAlloc = function() { abort('cannot dynamically allocate, sbrk now has control') };
02789       }
02790       var ret = DYNAMICTOP;
02791       if (bytes != 0) self.alloc(bytes);
02792       return ret;  // Previous break location.
02793     }

02803   function ___cxa_is_number_type(type) {
02804       var isNumber = false;
02805       try { if (type == __ZTIi) isNumber = true } catch(e){}
02806       try { if (type == __ZTIj) isNumber = true } catch(e){}
02807       try { if (type == __ZTIl) isNumber = true } catch(e){}
02808       try { if (type == __ZTIm) isNumber = true } catch(e){}
02809       try { if (type == __ZTIx) isNumber = true } catch(e){}
02810       try { if (type == __ZTIy) isNumber = true } catch(e){}
02811       try { if (type == __ZTIf) isNumber = true } catch(e){}
02812       try { if (type == __ZTId) isNumber = true } catch(e){}
02813       try { if (type == __ZTIe) isNumber = true } catch(e){}
02814       try { if (type == __ZTIc) isNumber = true } catch(e){}
02815       try { if (type == __ZTIa) isNumber = true } catch(e){}
02816       try { if (type == __ZTIh) isNumber = true } catch(e){}
02817       try { if (type == __ZTIs) isNumber = true } catch(e){}
02818       try { if (type == __ZTIt) isNumber = true } catch(e){}
02819       return isNumber;
02820     }function ___cxa_does_inherit(definiteType, possibilityType, possibility) {
02821       if (possibility == 0) return false;
02822       if (possibilityType == 0 || possibilityType == definiteType)
02823         return true;
02824       var possibility_type_info;
02825       if (___cxa_is_number_type(possibilityType)) {
02826         possibility_type_info = possibilityType;
02827       } else {
02828         var possibility_type_infoAddr = HEAP32[((possibilityType)>>2)] - 8;
02829         possibility_type_info = HEAP32[((possibility_type_infoAddr)>>2)];
02830       }
02831       switch (possibility_type_info) {
02832       case 0: // possibility is a pointer
02833         // See if definite type is a pointer
02834         var definite_type_infoAddr = HEAP32[((definiteType)>>2)] - 8;
02835         var definite_type_info = HEAP32[((definite_type_infoAddr)>>2)];
02836         if (definite_type_info == 0) {
02837           // Also a pointer; compare base types of pointers
02838           var defPointerBaseAddr = definiteType+8;
02839           var defPointerBaseType = HEAP32[((defPointerBaseAddr)>>2)];
02840           var possPointerBaseAddr = possibilityType+8;
02841           var possPointerBaseType = HEAP32[((possPointerBaseAddr)>>2)];
02842           return ___cxa_does_inherit(defPointerBaseType, possPointerBaseType, possibility);
02843         } else
02844           return false; // one pointer and one non-pointer
02845       case 1: // class with no base class
02846         return false;
02847       case 2: // class with base class
02848         var parentTypeAddr = possibilityType + 8;
02849         var parentType = HEAP32[((parentTypeAddr)>>2)];
02850         return ___cxa_does_inherit(definiteType, parentType, possibility);
02851       default:
02852         return false; // some unencountered type
02853       }
02854     }
02855   function ___resumeException(ptr) {
02856       if (HEAP32[((_llvm_eh_exception.buf)>>2)] == 0) HEAP32[((_llvm_eh_exception.buf)>>2)]=ptr;
02857       throw ptr + " - Exception catching is disabled, this exception cannot be caught. Compile with -s DISABLE_EXCEPTION_CATCHING=0 or DISABLE_EXCEPTION_CATCHING=2 to catch.";;
02858     }function ___cxa_find_matching_catch(thrown, throwntype) {
02859       if (thrown == -1) thrown = HEAP32[((_llvm_eh_exception.buf)>>2)];
02860       if (throwntype == -1) throwntype = HEAP32[(((_llvm_eh_exception.buf)+(4))>>2)];
02861       var typeArray = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments, 2);
02862       // If throwntype is a pointer, this means a pointer has been
02863       // thrown. When a pointer is thrown, actually what's thrown
02864       // is a pointer to the pointer. We'll dereference it.
02865       if (throwntype != 0 && !___cxa_is_number_type(throwntype)) {
02866         var throwntypeInfoAddr= HEAP32[((throwntype)>>2)] - 8;
02867         var throwntypeInfo= HEAP32[((throwntypeInfoAddr)>>2)];
02868         if (throwntypeInfo == 0)
02869           thrown = HEAP32[((thrown)>>2)];
02870       }
02871       // The different catch blocks are denoted by different types.
02872       // Due to inheritance, those types may not precisely match the
02873       // type of the thrown object. Find one which matches, and
02874       // return the type of the catch block which should be called.
02875       for (var i = 0; i < typeArray.length; i++) {
02876         if (___cxa_does_inherit(typeArray[i], throwntype, thrown))
02877           return ((asm["setTempRet0"](typeArray[i]),thrown)|0);
02878       }
02879       // Shouldn't happen unless we have bogus data in typeArray
02880       // or encounter a type for which emscripten doesn't have suitable
02881       // typeinfo defined. Best-efforts match just in case.
02882       return ((asm["setTempRet0"](throwntype),thrown)|0);
02883     }function ___cxa_throw(ptr, type, destructor) {
02884       if (!___cxa_throw.initialized) {
02885         try {
02886           HEAP32[((__ZTVN10__cxxabiv119__pointer_type_infoE)>>2)]=0; // Workaround for libcxxabi integration bug
02887         } catch(e){}
02888         try {
02889           HEAP32[((__ZTVN10__cxxabiv117__class_type_infoE)>>2)]=1; // Workaround for libcxxabi integration bug
02890         } catch(e){}
02891         try {
02892           HEAP32[((__ZTVN10__cxxabiv120__si_class_type_infoE)>>2)]=2; // Workaround for libcxxabi integration bug
02893         } catch(e){}
02894         ___cxa_throw.initialized = true;
02895       }
02896       HEAP32[((_llvm_eh_exception.buf)>>2)]=ptr
02897       HEAP32[(((_llvm_eh_exception.buf)+(4))>>2)]=type
02898       HEAP32[(((_llvm_eh_exception.buf)+(8))>>2)]=destructor
02899       if (!("uncaught_exception" in __ZSt18uncaught_exceptionv)) {
02900         __ZSt18uncaught_exceptionv.uncaught_exception = 1;
02901       } else {
02902         __ZSt18uncaught_exceptionv.uncaught_exception++;
02903       }
02904       throw ptr + " - Exception catching is disabled, this exception cannot be caught. Compile with -s DISABLE_EXCEPTION_CATCHING=0 or DISABLE_EXCEPTION_CATCHING=2 to catch.";;
02905     }
