02942   var _environ=allocate(1, "i32*", ALLOC_STATIC);var ___environ=_environ;function ___buildEnvironment(env) {
02943       // WARNING: Arbitrary limit!
02944       var MAX_ENV_VALUES = 64;
02945       var TOTAL_ENV_SIZE = 1024;
02946       // Statically allocate memory for the environment.
02947       var poolPtr;
02948       var envPtr;
02949       if (!___buildEnvironment.called) {
02950         ___buildEnvironment.called = true;
02951         // Set default values. Use string keys for Closure Compiler compatibility.
02952         ENV['USER'] = 'root';
02953         ENV['PATH'] = '/';
02954         ENV['PWD'] = '/';
02955         ENV['HOME'] = '/home/emscripten';
02956         ENV['LANG'] = 'en_US.UTF-8';
02957         ENV['_'] = './this.program';
02958         // Allocate memory.
02959         poolPtr = allocate(TOTAL_ENV_SIZE, 'i8', ALLOC_STATIC);
02960         envPtr = allocate(MAX_ENV_VALUES * 4,
02961                           'i8*', ALLOC_STATIC);
02962         HEAP32[((envPtr)>>2)]=poolPtr
02963         HEAP32[((_environ)>>2)]=envPtr;
02964       } else {
02965         envPtr = HEAP32[((_environ)>>2)];
02966         poolPtr = HEAP32[((envPtr)>>2)];
02967       }
02968       // Collect key=value lines.
02969       var strings = [];
02970       var totalSize = 0;
02971       for (var key in env) {
02972         if (typeof env[key] === 'string') {
02973           var line = key + '=' + env[key];
02974           strings.push(line);
02975           totalSize += line.length;
02976         }
02977       }
02978       if (totalSize > TOTAL_ENV_SIZE) {
02979         throw new Error('Environment size exceeded TOTAL_ENV_SIZE!');
02980       }
02981       // Make new.
02982       var ptrSize = 4;
02983       for (var i = 0; i < strings.length; i++) {
02984         var line = strings[i];
02985         for (var j = 0; j < line.length; j++) {
02986           HEAP8[(((poolPtr)+(j))|0)]=line.charCodeAt(j);
02987         }
02988         HEAP8[(((poolPtr)+(j))|0)]=0;
02989         HEAP32[(((envPtr)+(i * ptrSize))>>2)]=poolPtr;
02990         poolPtr += line.length + 1;
02991       }
02992       HEAP32[(((envPtr)+(strings.length * ptrSize))>>2)]=0;

02996       if (name === 0) return 0;

02998       if (!ENV.hasOwnProperty(name)) return 0;
02999       if (_getenv.ret) _free(_getenv.ret);
03000       _getenv.ret = allocate(intArrayFromString(ENV[name]), 'i8', ALLOC_NORMAL);
03001       return _getenv.ret;
03002     }

03165               function encode64(data) {
03166                 var BASE = 'ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789+/';
03167                 var PAD = '=';
03168                 var ret = '';
03169                 var leftchar = 0;
03170                 var leftbits = 0;
03171                 for (var i = 0; i < data.length; i++) {
03172                   leftchar = (leftchar << 8) | data[i];
03173                   leftbits += 8;
03174                   while (leftbits >= 6) {
03175                     var curr = (leftchar >> (leftbits-6)) & 0x3f;
03176                     leftbits -= 6;
03177                     ret += BASE[curr];
03178                   }
03179                 }
03180                 if (leftbits == 2) {
03181                   ret += BASE[(leftchar&3) << 4];
03182                   ret += PAD + PAD;
03183                 } else if (leftbits == 4) {
03184                   ret += BASE[(leftchar&0xf) << 2];
03185                   ret += PAD;
03186                 }
03187                 return ret;
03188               }
03189               audio.src = 'data:audio/x-' + name.substr(-3) + ';base64,' + encode64(byteArray);
03190               finish(audio); // we don't wait for confirmation this worked - but it's worth trying
03191             };
03192             audio.src = url;
03193             // workaround for chrome bug 124926 - we do not always get oncanplaythrough or onerror
03194             Browser.safeSetTimeout(function() {
03195               finish(audio); // try to use it even though it is not necessarily ready to play
03196             }, 10000);
03197           } else {
03198             return fail();
03199           }

03344         if (Browser.pointerLock) {
03345           // When the pointer is locked, calculate the coordinates
03346           // based on the movement of the mouse.
03347           // Workaround for Firefox bug 764498
03348           if (event.type != 'mousemove' &&
03349               ('mozMovementX' in event)) {
03350             Browser.mouseMovementX = Browser.mouseMovementY = 0;
03351           } else {
03352             Browser.mouseMovementX = Browser.getMovementX(event);
03353             Browser.mouseMovementY = Browser.getMovementY(event);
03354           }
03355           // check if SDL is available
03356           if (typeof SDL != "undefined") {
03357             Browser.mouseX = SDL.mouseX + Browser.mouseMovementX;
03358             Browser.mouseY = SDL.mouseY + Browser.mouseMovementY;
03359           } else {
03360             // just add the mouse delta to the current absolut mouse position
03361             // FIXME: ideally this should be clamped against the canvas size and zero
03362             Browser.mouseX += Browser.mouseMovementX;
03363             Browser.mouseY += Browser.mouseMovementY;
03364           }
03365         } else {
03366           // Otherwise, calculate the movement based on the changes
03367           // in the coordinates.
03368           var rect = Module["canvas"].getBoundingClientRect();
03369           var x = event.pageX - (window.scrollX + rect.left);
03370           var y = event.pageY - (window.scrollY + rect.top);
03371           // the canvas might be CSS-scaled compared to its backbuffer;
03372           // SDL-using content will want mouse coordinates in terms
03373           // of backbuffer units.
03374           var cw = Module["canvas"].width;
03375           var ch = Module["canvas"].height;
03376           x = x * (cw / rect.width);
03377           y = y * (ch / rect.height);
03378           Browser.mouseMovementX = x - Browser.mouseX;
03379           Browser.mouseMovementY = y - Browser.mouseY;
03380           Browser.mouseX = x;
03381           Browser.mouseY = y;
03382         }

27020 var i64Math = (function() { // Emscripten wrapper
27021   var goog = { math: {} };
27045   goog.math.Long = function(low, high) {
27050     this.low_ = low | 0;  // force into 32 signed bits.
27055     this.high_ = high | 0;  // force into 32 signed bits.
27056   };
27057   // NOTE: Common constant values ZERO, ONE, NEG_ONE, etc. are defined below the
27058   // from* methods on which they depend.
27064   goog.math.Long.IntCache_ = {};
27070   goog.math.Long.fromInt = function(value) {
27071     if (-128 <= value && value < 128) {
27072       var cachedObj = goog.math.Long.IntCache_[value];
27073       if (cachedObj) {
27074         return cachedObj;
27075       }
27076     }
27077     var obj = new goog.math.Long(value | 0, value < 0 ? -1 : 0);
27078     if (-128 <= value && value < 128) {
27079       goog.math.Long.IntCache_[value] = obj;
27080     }
27081     return obj;
27082   };
27089   goog.math.Long.fromNumber = function(value) {
27090     if (isNaN(value) || !isFinite(value)) {
27091       return goog.math.Long.ZERO;
27092     } else if (value <= -goog.math.Long.TWO_PWR_63_DBL_) {
27093       return goog.math.Long.MIN_VALUE;
27094     } else if (value + 1 >= goog.math.Long.TWO_PWR_63_DBL_) {
27095       return goog.math.Long.MAX_VALUE;
27096     } else if (value < 0) {
27097       return goog.math.Long.fromNumber(-value).negate();
27098     } else {
27099       return new goog.math.Long(
27100           (value % goog.math.Long.TWO_PWR_32_DBL_) | 0,
27101           (value / goog.math.Long.TWO_PWR_32_DBL_) | 0);
27102     }
27103   };
27111   goog.math.Long.fromBits = function(lowBits, highBits) {
27112     return new goog.math.Long(lowBits, highBits);
27113   };
27121   goog.math.Long.fromString = function(str, opt_radix) {
27122     if (str.length == 0) {
27123       throw Error('number format error: empty string');
27124     }
27125     var radix = opt_radix || 10;
27126     if (radix < 2 || 36 < radix) {
27127       throw Error('radix out of range: ' + radix);
27128     }
27129     if (str.charAt(0) == '-') {
27130       return goog.math.Long.fromString(str.substring(1), radix).negate();
27131     } else if (str.indexOf('-') >= 0) {
27132       throw Error('number format error: interior "-" character: ' + str);
27133     }
27134     // Do several (8) digits each time through the loop, so as to
27135     // minimize the calls to the very expensive emulated div.
27136     var radixToPower = goog.math.Long.fromNumber(Math.pow(radix, 8));
27137     var result = goog.math.Long.ZERO;
27138     for (var i = 0; i < str.length; i += 8) {
27139       var size = Math.min(8, str.length - i);
27140       var value = parseInt(str.substring(i, i + size), radix);
27141       if (size < 8) {
27142         var power = goog.math.Long.fromNumber(Math.pow(radix, size));
27143         result = result.multiply(power).add(goog.math.Long.fromNumber(value));
27144       } else {
27145         result = result.multiply(radixToPower);
27146         result = result.add(goog.math.Long.fromNumber(value));
27147       }
27148     }
27149     return result;
27150   };
27151   // NOTE: the compiler should inline these constant values below and then remove
27152   // these variables, so there should be no runtime penalty for these.
27159   goog.math.Long.TWO_PWR_16_DBL_ = 1 << 16;
27164   goog.math.Long.TWO_PWR_24_DBL_ = 1 << 24;
27169   goog.math.Long.TWO_PWR_32_DBL_ =
27170       goog.math.Long.TWO_PWR_16_DBL_ * goog.math.Long.TWO_PWR_16_DBL_;
27175   goog.math.Long.TWO_PWR_31_DBL_ =
27176       goog.math.Long.TWO_PWR_32_DBL_ / 2;
27181   goog.math.Long.TWO_PWR_48_DBL_ =
27182       goog.math.Long.TWO_PWR_32_DBL_ * goog.math.Long.TWO_PWR_16_DBL_;
27187   goog.math.Long.TWO_PWR_64_DBL_ =
27188       goog.math.Long.TWO_PWR_32_DBL_ * goog.math.Long.TWO_PWR_32_DBL_;
27193   goog.math.Long.TWO_PWR_63_DBL_ =
27194       goog.math.Long.TWO_PWR_64_DBL_ / 2;
27196   goog.math.Long.ZERO = goog.math.Long.fromInt(0);
27198   goog.math.Long.ONE = goog.math.Long.fromInt(1);
27200   goog.math.Long.NEG_ONE = goog.math.Long.fromInt(-1);
27202   goog.math.Long.MAX_VALUE =
27203       goog.math.Long.fromBits(0xFFFFFFFF | 0, 0x7FFFFFFF | 0);
27205   goog.math.Long.MIN_VALUE = goog.math.Long.fromBits(0, 0x80000000 | 0);
27210   goog.math.Long.TWO_PWR_24_ = goog.math.Long.fromInt(1 << 24);
27212   goog.math.Long.prototype.toInt = function() {
27213     return this.low_;
27214   };
27216   goog.math.Long.prototype.toNumber = function() {
27217     return this.high_ * goog.math.Long.TWO_PWR_32_DBL_ +
27218            this.getLowBitsUnsigned();
27219   };
27224   goog.math.Long.prototype.toString = function(opt_radix) {
27225     var radix = opt_radix || 10;
27226     if (radix < 2 || 36 < radix) {
27227       throw Error('radix out of range: ' + radix);
27228     }
27229     if (this.isZero()) {
27230       return '0';
27231     }
27232     if (this.isNegative()) {
27233       if (this.equals(goog.math.Long.MIN_VALUE)) {
27234         // We need to change the Long value before it can be negated, so we remove
27235         // the bottom-most digit in this base and then recurse to do the rest.
27236         var radixLong = goog.math.Long.fromNumber(radix);
27237         var div = this.div(radixLong);
27238         var rem = div.multiply(radixLong).subtract(this);
27239         return div.toString(radix) + rem.toInt().toString(radix);
27240       } else {
27241         return '-' + this.negate().toString(radix);
27242       }
27243     }
27244     // Do several (6) digits each time through the loop, so as to
27245     // minimize the calls to the very expensive emulated div.
27246     var radixToPower = goog.math.Long.fromNumber(Math.pow(radix, 6));
27247     var rem = this;
27248     var result = '';
27249     while (true) {
27250       var remDiv = rem.div(radixToPower);
27251       var intval = rem.subtract(remDiv.multiply(radixToPower)).toInt();
27252       var digits = intval.toString(radix);
27253       rem = remDiv;
27254       if (rem.isZero()) {
27255         return digits + result;
27256       } else {
27257         while (digits.length < 6) {
27258           digits = '0' + digits;
27259         }
27260         result = '' + digits + result;
27261       }
27262     }
27263   };
27265   goog.math.Long.prototype.getHighBits = function() {
27266     return this.high_;
27267   };
27269   goog.math.Long.prototype.getLowBits = function() {
27270     return this.low_;
27271   };
27273   goog.math.Long.prototype.getLowBitsUnsigned = function() {
27274     return (this.low_ >= 0) ?
27275         this.low_ : goog.math.Long.TWO_PWR_32_DBL_ + this.low_;
27276   };
27281   goog.math.Long.prototype.getNumBitsAbs = function() {
27282     if (this.isNegative()) {
27283       if (this.equals(goog.math.Long.MIN_VALUE)) {
27284         return 64;
27285       } else {
27286         return this.negate().getNumBitsAbs();
27287       }
27288     } else {
27289       var val = this.high_ != 0 ? this.high_ : this.low_;
27290       for (var bit = 31; bit > 0; bit--) {
27291         if ((val & (1 << bit)) != 0) {
27292           break;
27293         }
27294       }
27295       return this.high_ != 0 ? bit + 33 : bit + 1;
27296     }
27297   };
27299   goog.math.Long.prototype.isZero = function() {
27300     return this.high_ == 0 && this.low_ == 0;
27301   };
27303   goog.math.Long.prototype.isNegative = function() {
27304     return this.high_ < 0;
27305   };
27307   goog.math.Long.prototype.isOdd = function() {
27308     return (this.low_ & 1) == 1;
27309   };
27314   goog.math.Long.prototype.equals = function(other) {
27315     return (this.high_ == other.high_) && (this.low_ == other.low_);
27316   };
27321   goog.math.Long.prototype.notEquals = function(other) {
27322     return (this.high_ != other.high_) || (this.low_ != other.low_);
27323   };
27328   goog.math.Long.prototype.lessThan = function(other) {
27329     return this.compare(other) < 0;
27330   };
27335   goog.math.Long.prototype.lessThanOrEqual = function(other) {
27336     return this.compare(other) <= 0;
27337   };
27342   goog.math.Long.prototype.greaterThan = function(other) {
27343     return this.compare(other) > 0;
27344   };
27349   goog.math.Long.prototype.greaterThanOrEqual = function(other) {
27350     return this.compare(other) >= 0;
27351   };
27358   goog.math.Long.prototype.compare = function(other) {
27359     if (this.equals(other)) {
27360       return 0;
27361     }
27362     var thisNeg = this.isNegative();
27363     var otherNeg = other.isNegative();
27364     if (thisNeg && !otherNeg) {
27365       return -1;
27366     }
27367     if (!thisNeg && otherNeg) {
27368       return 1;
27369     }
27370     // at this point, the signs are the same, so subtraction will not overflow
27371     if (this.subtract(other).isNegative()) {
27372       return -1;
27373     } else {
27374       return 1;
27375     }
27376   };
27378   goog.math.Long.prototype.negate = function() {
27379     if (this.equals(goog.math.Long.MIN_VALUE)) {
27380       return goog.math.Long.MIN_VALUE;
27381     } else {
27382       return this.not().add(goog.math.Long.ONE);
27383     }
27384   };
27390   goog.math.Long.prototype.add = function(other) {
27391     // Divide each number into 4 chunks of 16 bits, and then sum the chunks.
27392     var a48 = this.high_ >>> 16;
27393     var a32 = this.high_ & 0xFFFF;
27394     var a16 = this.low_ >>> 16;
27395     var a00 = this.low_ & 0xFFFF;
27396     var b48 = other.high_ >>> 16;
27397     var b32 = other.high_ & 0xFFFF;
27398     var b16 = other.low_ >>> 16;
27399     var b00 = other.low_ & 0xFFFF;
27400     var c48 = 0, c32 = 0, c16 = 0, c00 = 0;
27401     c00 += a00 + b00;
27402     c16 += c00 >>> 16;
27403     c00 &= 0xFFFF;
27404     c16 += a16 + b16;
27405     c32 += c16 >>> 16;
27406     c16 &= 0xFFFF;
27407     c32 += a32 + b32;
27408     c48 += c32 >>> 16;
27409     c32 &= 0xFFFF;
27410     c48 += a48 + b48;
27411     c48 &= 0xFFFF;
27412     return goog.math.Long.fromBits((c16 << 16) | c00, (c48 << 16) | c32);
27413   };
27419   goog.math.Long.prototype.subtract = function(other) {
27420     return this.add(other.negate());
27421   };
27427   goog.math.Long.prototype.multiply = function(other) {
27428     if (this.isZero()) {
27429       return goog.math.Long.ZERO;
27430     } else if (other.isZero()) {
27431       return goog.math.Long.ZERO;
27432     }
27433     if (this.equals(goog.math.Long.MIN_VALUE)) {
27434       return other.isOdd() ? goog.math.Long.MIN_VALUE : goog.math.Long.ZERO;
27435     } else if (other.equals(goog.math.Long.MIN_VALUE)) {
27436       return this.isOdd() ? goog.math.Long.MIN_VALUE : goog.math.Long.ZERO;
27437     }
27438     if (this.isNegative()) {
27439       if (other.isNegative()) {
27440         return this.negate().multiply(other.negate());
27441       } else {
27442         return this.negate().multiply(other).negate();
27443       }
27444     } else if (other.isNegative()) {
27445       return this.multiply(other.negate()).negate();
27446     }
27447     // If both longs are small, use float multiplication
27448     if (this.lessThan(goog.math.Long.TWO_PWR_24_) &&
27449         other.lessThan(goog.math.Long.TWO_PWR_24_)) {
27450       return goog.math.Long.fromNumber(this.toNumber() * other.toNumber());
27451     }
27452     // Divide each long into 4 chunks of 16 bits, and then add up 4x4 products.
27453     // We can skip products that would overflow.
27454     var a48 = this.high_ >>> 16;
27455     var a32 = this.high_ & 0xFFFF;
27456     var a16 = this.low_ >>> 16;
27457     var a00 = this.low_ & 0xFFFF;
27458     var b48 = other.high_ >>> 16;
27459     var b32 = other.high_ & 0xFFFF;
27460     var b16 = other.low_ >>> 16;
27461     var b00 = other.low_ & 0xFFFF;
27462     var c48 = 0, c32 = 0, c16 = 0, c00 = 0;
27463     c00 += a00 * b00;
27464     c16 += c00 >>> 16;
27465     c00 &= 0xFFFF;
27466     c16 += a16 * b00;
27467     c32 += c16 >>> 16;
27468     c16 &= 0xFFFF;
27469     c16 += a00 * b16;
27470     c32 += c16 >>> 16;
27471     c16 &= 0xFFFF;
27472     c32 += a32 * b00;
27473     c48 += c32 >>> 16;
27474     c32 &= 0xFFFF;
27475     c32 += a16 * b16;
27476     c48 += c32 >>> 16;
27477     c32 &= 0xFFFF;
27478     c32 += a00 * b32;
27479     c48 += c32 >>> 16;
27480     c32 &= 0xFFFF;
27481     c48 += a48 * b00 + a32 * b16 + a16 * b32 + a00 * b48;
27482     c48 &= 0xFFFF;
27483     return goog.math.Long.fromBits((c16 << 16) | c00, (c48 << 16) | c32);
27484   };
27490   goog.math.Long.prototype.div = function(other) {
27491     if (other.isZero()) {
27492       throw Error('division by zero');
27493     } else if (this.isZero()) {
27494       return goog.math.Long.ZERO;
27495     }
27496     if (this.equals(goog.math.Long.MIN_VALUE)) {
27497       if (other.equals(goog.math.Long.ONE) ||
27498           other.equals(goog.math.Long.NEG_ONE)) {
27499         return goog.math.Long.MIN_VALUE;  // recall that -MIN_VALUE == MIN_VALUE
27500       } else if (other.equals(goog.math.Long.MIN_VALUE)) {
27501         return goog.math.Long.ONE;
27502       } else {
27503         // At this point, we have |other| >= 2, so |this/other| < |MIN_VALUE|.
27504         var halfThis = this.shiftRight(1);
27505         var approx = halfThis.div(other).shiftLeft(1);
27506         if (approx.equals(goog.math.Long.ZERO)) {
27507           return other.isNegative() ? goog.math.Long.ONE : goog.math.Long.NEG_ONE;
27508         } else {
27509           var rem = this.subtract(other.multiply(approx));
27510           var result = approx.add(rem.div(other));
27511           return result;
27512         }
27513       }
27514     } else if (other.equals(goog.math.Long.MIN_VALUE)) {
27515       return goog.math.Long.ZERO;
27516     }
27517     if (this.isNegative()) {
27518       if (other.isNegative()) {
27519         return this.negate().div(other.negate());
27520       } else {
27521         return this.negate().div(other).negate();
27522       }
27523     } else if (other.isNegative()) {
27524       return this.div(other.negate()).negate();
27525     }
27526     // Repeat the following until the remainder is less than other:  find a
27527     // floating-point that approximates remainder / other *from below*, add this
27528     // into the result, and subtract it from the remainder.  It is critical that
27529     // the approximate value is less than or equal to the real value so that the
27530     // remainder never becomes negative.
27531     var res = goog.math.Long.ZERO;
27532     var rem = this;
27533     while (rem.greaterThanOrEqual(other)) {
27534       // Approximate the result of division. This may be a little greater or
27535       // smaller than the actual value.
27536       var approx = Math.max(1, Math.floor(rem.toNumber() / other.toNumber()));
27537       // We will tweak the approximate result by changing it in the 48-th digit or
27538       // the smallest non-fractional digit, whichever is larger.
27539       var log2 = Math.ceil(Math.log(approx) / Math.LN2);
27540       var delta = (log2 <= 48) ? 1 : Math.pow(2, log2 - 48);
27541       // Decrease the approximation until it is smaller than the remainder.  Note
27542       // that if it is too large, the product overflows and is negative.
27543       var approxRes = goog.math.Long.fromNumber(approx);
27544       var approxRem = approxRes.multiply(other);
27545       while (approxRem.isNegative() || approxRem.greaterThan(rem)) {
27546         approx -= delta;
27547         approxRes = goog.math.Long.fromNumber(approx);
27548         approxRem = approxRes.multiply(other);
27549       }
27550       // We know the answer can't be zero... and actually, zero would cause
27551       // infinite recursion since we would make no progress.
27552       if (approxRes.isZero()) {
27553         approxRes = goog.math.Long.ONE;
27554       }
27555       res = res.add(approxRes);
27556       rem = rem.subtract(approxRem);
27557     }
27558     return res;
27559   };
27565   goog.math.Long.prototype.modulo = function(other) {
27566     return this.subtract(this.div(other).multiply(other));
27567   };
27569   goog.math.Long.prototype.not = function() {
27570     return goog.math.Long.fromBits(~this.low_, ~this.high_);
27571   };
27577   goog.math.Long.prototype.and = function(other) {
27578     return goog.math.Long.fromBits(this.low_ & other.low_,
27579                                    this.high_ & other.high_);
27580   };
27586   goog.math.Long.prototype.or = function(other) {
27587     return goog.math.Long.fromBits(this.low_ | other.low_,
27588                                    this.high_ | other.high_);
27589   };
27595   goog.math.Long.prototype.xor = function(other) {
27596     return goog.math.Long.fromBits(this.low_ ^ other.low_,
27597                                    this.high_ ^ other.high_);
27598   };
27604   goog.math.Long.prototype.shiftLeft = function(numBits) {
27605     numBits &= 63;
27606     if (numBits == 0) {
27607       return this;
27608     } else {
27609       var low = this.low_;
27610       if (numBits < 32) {
27611         var high = this.high_;
27612         return goog.math.Long.fromBits(
27613             low << numBits,
27614             (high << numBits) | (low >>> (32 - numBits)));
27615       } else {
27616         return goog.math.Long.fromBits(0, low << (numBits - 32));
27617       }
27618     }
27619   };
27625   goog.math.Long.prototype.shiftRight = function(numBits) {
27626     numBits &= 63;
27627     if (numBits == 0) {
27628       return this;
27629     } else {
27630       var high = this.high_;
27631       if (numBits < 32) {
27632         var low = this.low_;
27633         return goog.math.Long.fromBits(
27634             (low >>> numBits) | (high << (32 - numBits)),
27635             high >> numBits);
27636       } else {
27637         return goog.math.Long.fromBits(
27638             high >> (numBits - 32),
27639             high >= 0 ? 0 : -1);
27640       }
27641     }
27642   };
27650   goog.math.Long.prototype.shiftRightUnsigned = function(numBits) {
27651     numBits &= 63;
27652     if (numBits == 0) {
27653       return this;
27654     } else {
27655       var high = this.high_;
27656       if (numBits < 32) {
27657         var low = this.low_;
27658         return goog.math.Long.fromBits(
27659             (low >>> numBits) | (high << (32 - numBits)),
27660             high >>> numBits);
27661       } else if (numBits == 32) {
27662         return goog.math.Long.fromBits(high, 0);
27663       } else {
27664         return goog.math.Long.fromBits(high >>> (numBits - 32), 0);
27665       }
27666     }
27667   };

27703   // Basic JavaScript BN library - subset useful for RSA encryption.
27704   // Bits per digit
27705   var dbits;
27706   // JavaScript engine analysis
27707   var canary = 0xdeadbeefcafe;
27708   var j_lm = ((canary&0xffffff)==0xefcafe);
27709   // (public) Constructor
27710   function BigInteger(a,b,c) {
27711     if(a != null)
27712       if("number" == typeof a) this.fromNumber(a,b,c);
27713       else if(b == null && "string" != typeof a) this.fromString(a,256);
27714       else this.fromString(a,b);
27715   }
27716   // return new, unset BigInteger
27717   function nbi() { return new BigInteger(null); }
27718   // am: Compute w_j += (x*this_i), propagate carries,
27719   // c is initial carry, returns final carry.
27720   // c < 3*dvalue, x < 2*dvalue, this_i < dvalue
27721   // We need to select the fastest one that works in this environment.
27722   // am1: use a single mult and divide to get the high bits,
27723   // max digit bits should be 26 because
27724   // max internal value = 2*dvalue^2-2*dvalue (< 2^53)
27725   function am1(i,x,w,j,c,n) {
27726     while(--n >= 0) {
27727       var v = x*this[i++]+w[j]+c;
27728       c = Math.floor(v/0x4000000);
27729       w[j++] = v&0x3ffffff;
27730     }
27731     return c;
27732   }
27733   // am2 avoids a big mult-and-extract completely.
27734   // Max digit bits should be <= 30 because we do bitwise ops
27735   // on values up to 2*hdvalue^2-hdvalue-1 (< 2^31)
27736   function am2(i,x,w,j,c,n) {
27737     var xl = x&0x7fff, xh = x>>15;
27738     while(--n >= 0) {
27739       var l = this[i]&0x7fff;
27740       var h = this[i++]>>15;
27741       var m = xh*l+h*xl;
27742       l = xl*l+((m&0x7fff)<<15)+w[j]+(c&0x3fffffff);
27743       c = (l>>>30)+(m>>>15)+xh*h+(c>>>30);
27744       w[j++] = l&0x3fffffff;
27745     }
27746     return c;
27747   }
27748   // Alternately, set max digit bits to 28 since some
27749   // browsers slow down when dealing with 32-bit numbers.
27750   function am3(i,x,w,j,c,n) {
27751     var xl = x&0x3fff, xh = x>>14;
27752     while(--n >= 0) {
27753       var l = this[i]&0x3fff;
27754       var h = this[i++]>>14;
27755       var m = xh*l+h*xl;
27756       l = xl*l+((m&0x3fff)<<14)+w[j]+c;
27757       c = (l>>28)+(m>>14)+xh*h;
27758       w[j++] = l&0xfffffff;
27759     }
27760     return c;
27761   }
27762   if(j_lm && (navigator.appName == "Microsoft Internet Explorer")) {
27763     BigInteger.prototype.am = am2;
27764     dbits = 30;
27765   }
27766   else if(j_lm && (navigator.appName != "Netscape")) {
27767     BigInteger.prototype.am = am1;
27768     dbits = 26;
27769   }
27770   else { // Mozilla/Netscape seems to prefer am3
27771     BigInteger.prototype.am = am3;
27772     dbits = 28;
27773   }
27774   BigInteger.prototype.DB = dbits;
27775   BigInteger.prototype.DM = ((1<<dbits)-1);
27776   BigInteger.prototype.DV = (1<<dbits);
27777   var BI_FP = 52;
27778   BigInteger.prototype.FV = Math.pow(2,BI_FP);
27779   BigInteger.prototype.F1 = BI_FP-dbits;
27780   BigInteger.prototype.F2 = 2*dbits-BI_FP;
27781   // Digit conversions
27782   var BI_RM = "0123456789abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz";
27783   var BI_RC = new Array();
27784   var rr,vv;
27785   rr = "0".charCodeAt(0);
27786   for(vv = 0; vv <= 9; ++vv) BI_RC[rr++] = vv;
27787   rr = "a".charCodeAt(0);
27788   for(vv = 10; vv < 36; ++vv) BI_RC[rr++] = vv;
27789   rr = "A".charCodeAt(0);
27790   for(vv = 10; vv < 36; ++vv) BI_RC[rr++] = vv;
27791   function int2char(n) { return BI_RM.charAt(n); }
27792   function intAt(s,i) {
27793     var c = BI_RC[s.charCodeAt(i)];
27794     return (c==null)?-1:c;
27795   }
27796   // (protected) copy this to r
27797   function bnpCopyTo(r) {
27798     for(var i = this.t-1; i >= 0; --i) r[i] = this[i];
27799     r.t = this.t;
27800     r.s = this.s;
27801   }
27802   // (protected) set from integer value x, -DV <= x < DV
27803   function bnpFromInt(x) {
27804     this.t = 1;
27805     this.s = (x<0)?-1:0;
27806     if(x > 0) this[0] = x;
27807     else if(x < -1) this[0] = x+DV;
27808     else this.t = 0;
27809   }
27810   // return bigint initialized to value
27811   function nbv(i) { var r = nbi(); r.fromInt(i); return r; }
27812   // (protected) set from string and radix
27813   function bnpFromString(s,b) {
27814     var k;
27815     if(b == 16) k = 4;
27816     else if(b == 8) k = 3;
27817     else if(b == 256) k = 8; // byte array
27818     else if(b == 2) k = 1;
27819     else if(b == 32) k = 5;
27820     else if(b == 4) k = 2;
27821     else { this.fromRadix(s,b); return; }
27822     this.t = 0;
27823     this.s = 0;
27824     var i = s.length, mi = false, sh = 0;
27825     while(--i >= 0) {
27826       var x = (k==8)?s[i]&0xff:intAt(s,i);
27827       if(x < 0) {
27828         if(s.charAt(i) == "-") mi = true;
27829         continue;
27830       }
27831       mi = false;
27832       if(sh == 0)
27833         this[this.t++] = x;
27834       else if(sh+k > this.DB) {
27835         this[this.t-1] |= (x&((1<<(this.DB-sh))-1))<<sh;
27836         this[this.t++] = (x>>(this.DB-sh));
27837       }
27838       else
27839         this[this.t-1] |= x<<sh;
27840       sh += k;
27841       if(sh >= this.DB) sh -= this.DB;
27842     }
27843     if(k == 8 && (s[0]&0x80) != 0) {
27844       this.s = -1;
27845       if(sh > 0) this[this.t-1] |= ((1<<(this.DB-sh))-1)<<sh;
27846     }
27847     this.clamp();
27848     if(mi) BigInteger.ZERO.subTo(this,this);
27849   }
27850   // (protected) clamp off excess high words
27851   function bnpClamp() {
27852     var c = this.s&this.DM;
27853     while(this.t > 0 && this[this.t-1] == c) --this.t;
27854   }
27855   // (public) return string representation in given radix
27856   function bnToString(b) {
27857     if(this.s < 0) return "-"+this.negate().toString(b);
27858     var k;
27859     if(b == 16) k = 4;
27860     else if(b == 8) k = 3;
27861     else if(b == 2) k = 1;
27862     else if(b == 32) k = 5;
27863     else if(b == 4) k = 2;
27864     else return this.toRadix(b);
27865     var km = (1<<k)-1, d, m = false, r = "", i = this.t;
27866     var p = this.DB-(i*this.DB)%k;
27867     if(i-- > 0) {
27868       if(p < this.DB && (d = this[i]>>p) > 0) { m = true; r = int2char(d); }
27869       while(i >= 0) {
27870         if(p < k) {
27871           d = (this[i]&((1<<p)-1))<<(k-p);
27872           d |= this[--i]>>(p+=this.DB-k);
27873         }
27874         else {
27875           d = (this[i]>>(p-=k))&km;
27876           if(p <= 0) { p += this.DB; --i; }
27877         }
27878         if(d > 0) m = true;
27879         if(m) r += int2char(d);
27880       }
27881     }
27882     return m?r:"0";
27883   }
27884   // (public) -this
27885   function bnNegate() { var r = nbi(); BigInteger.ZERO.subTo(this,r); return r; }
27886   // (public) |this|
27887   function bnAbs() { return (this.s<0)?this.negate():this; }
27888   // (public) return + if this > a, - if this < a, 0 if equal
27889   function bnCompareTo(a) {
27890     var r = this.s-a.s;
27891     if(r != 0) return r;
27892     var i = this.t;
27893     r = i-a.t;
27894     if(r != 0) return (this.s<0)?-r:r;
27895     while(--i >= 0) if((r=this[i]-a[i]) != 0) return r;
27896     return 0;
27897   }
27898   // returns bit length of the integer x
27899   function nbits(x) {
27900     var r = 1, t;
27901     if((t=x>>>16) != 0) { x = t; r += 16; }
27902     if((t=x>>8) != 0) { x = t; r += 8; }
27903     if((t=x>>4) != 0) { x = t; r += 4; }
27904     if((t=x>>2) != 0) { x = t; r += 2; }
27905     if((t=x>>1) != 0) { x = t; r += 1; }
27906     return r;
27907   }
27908   // (public) return the number of bits in "this"
27909   function bnBitLength() {
27910     if(this.t <= 0) return 0;
27911     return this.DB*(this.t-1)+nbits(this[this.t-1]^(this.s&this.DM));
27912   }
27913   // (protected) r = this << n*DB
27914   function bnpDLShiftTo(n,r) {
27915     var i;
27916     for(i = this.t-1; i >= 0; --i) r[i+n] = this[i];
27917     for(i = n-1; i >= 0; --i) r[i] = 0;
27918     r.t = this.t+n;
27919     r.s = this.s;
27920   }
27921   // (protected) r = this >> n*DB
27922   function bnpDRShiftTo(n,r) {
27923     for(var i = n; i < this.t; ++i) r[i-n] = this[i];
27924     r.t = Math.max(this.t-n,0);
27925     r.s = this.s;
27926   }
27927   // (protected) r = this << n
27928   function bnpLShiftTo(n,r) {
27929     var bs = n%this.DB;
27930     var cbs = this.DB-bs;
27931     var bm = (1<<cbs)-1;
27932     var ds = Math.floor(n/this.DB), c = (this.s<<bs)&this.DM, i;
27933     for(i = this.t-1; i >= 0; --i) {
27934       r[i+ds+1] = (this[i]>>cbs)|c;
27935       c = (this[i]&bm)<<bs;
27936     }
27937     for(i = ds-1; i >= 0; --i) r[i] = 0;
27938     r[ds] = c;
27939     r.t = this.t+ds+1;
27940     r.s = this.s;
27941     r.clamp();
27942   }
27943   // (protected) r = this >> n
27944   function bnpRShiftTo(n,r) {
27945     r.s = this.s;
27946     var ds = Math.floor(n/this.DB);
27947     if(ds >= this.t) { r.t = 0; return; }
27948     var bs = n%this.DB;
27949     var cbs = this.DB-bs;
27950     var bm = (1<<bs)-1;
27951     r[0] = this[ds]>>bs;
27952     for(var i = ds+1; i < this.t; ++i) {
27953       r[i-ds-1] |= (this[i]&bm)<<cbs;
27954       r[i-ds] = this[i]>>bs;
27955     }
27956     if(bs > 0) r[this.t-ds-1] |= (this.s&bm)<<cbs;
27957     r.t = this.t-ds;
27958     r.clamp();
27959   }
27960   // (protected) r = this - a
27961   function bnpSubTo(a,r) {
27962     var i = 0, c = 0, m = Math.min(a.t,this.t);
27963     while(i < m) {
27964       c += this[i]-a[i];
27965       r[i++] = c&this.DM;
27966       c >>= this.DB;
27967     }
27968     if(a.t < this.t) {
27969       c -= a.s;
27970       while(i < this.t) {
27971         c += this[i];
27972         r[i++] = c&this.DM;
27973         c >>= this.DB;
27974       }
27975       c += this.s;
27976     }
27977     else {
27978       c += this.s;
27979       while(i < a.t) {
27980         c -= a[i];
27981         r[i++] = c&this.DM;
27982         c >>= this.DB;
27983       }
27984       c -= a.s;
27985     }
27986     r.s = (c<0)?-1:0;
27987     if(c < -1) r[i++] = this.DV+c;
27988     else if(c > 0) r[i++] = c;
27989     r.t = i;
27990     r.clamp();
27991   }
27992   // (protected) r = this * a, r != this,a (HAC 14.12)
27993   // "this" should be the larger one if appropriate.
27994   function bnpMultiplyTo(a,r) {
27995     var x = this.abs(), y = a.abs();
27996     var i = x.t;
27997     r.t = i+y.t;
27998     while(--i >= 0) r[i] = 0;
27999     for(i = 0; i < y.t; ++i) r[i+x.t] = x.am(0,y[i],r,i,0,x.t);
28000     r.s = 0;
28001     r.clamp();
28002     if(this.s != a.s) BigInteger.ZERO.subTo(r,r);
28003   }
28004   // (protected) r = this^2, r != this (HAC 14.16)
28005   function bnpSquareTo(r) {
28006     var x = this.abs();
28007     var i = r.t = 2*x.t;
28008     while(--i >= 0) r[i] = 0;
28009     for(i = 0; i < x.t-1; ++i) {
28010       var c = x.am(i,x[i],r,2*i,0,1);
28011       if((r[i+x.t]+=x.am(i+1,2*x[i],r,2*i+1,c,x.t-i-1)) >= x.DV) {
28012         r[i+x.t] -= x.DV;
28013         r[i+x.t+1] = 1;
28014       }
28015     }
28016     if(r.t > 0) r[r.t-1] += x.am(i,x[i],r,2*i,0,1);
28017     r.s = 0;
28018     r.clamp();
28019   }
28020   // (protected) divide this by m, quotient and remainder to q, r (HAC 14.20)
28021   // r != q, this != m.  q or r may be null.
28022   function bnpDivRemTo(m,q,r) {
28023     var pm = m.abs();
28024     if(pm.t <= 0) return;
28025     var pt = this.abs();
28026     if(pt.t < pm.t) {
28027       if(q != null) q.fromInt(0);
28028       if(r != null) this.copyTo(r);
28029       return;
28030     }
28031     if(r == null) r = nbi();
28032     var y = nbi(), ts = this.s, ms = m.s;
28033     var nsh = this.DB-nbits(pm[pm.t-1]);    // normalize modulus
28034     if(nsh > 0) { pm.lShiftTo(nsh,y); pt.lShiftTo(nsh,r); }
28035     else { pm.copyTo(y); pt.copyTo(r); }
28036     var ys = y.t;
28037     var y0 = y[ys-1];
28038     if(y0 == 0) return;
28039     var yt = y0*(1<<this.F1)+((ys>1)?y[ys-2]>>this.F2:0);
28040     var d1 = this.FV/yt, d2 = (1<<this.F1)/yt, e = 1<<this.F2;
28041     var i = r.t, j = i-ys, t = (q==null)?nbi():q;
28042     y.dlShiftTo(j,t);
28043     if(r.compareTo(t) >= 0) {
28044       r[r.t++] = 1;
28045       r.subTo(t,r);
28046     }
28047     BigInteger.ONE.dlShiftTo(ys,t);
28048     t.subTo(y,y);   // "negative" y so we can replace sub with am later
28049     while(y.t < ys) y[y.t++] = 0;
28050     while(--j >= 0) {
28051       // Estimate quotient digit
28052       var qd = (r[--i]==y0)?this.DM:Math.floor(r[i]*d1+(r[i-1]+e)*d2);
28053       if((r[i]+=y.am(0,qd,r,j,0,ys)) < qd) {    // Try it out
28054         y.dlShiftTo(j,t);
28055         r.subTo(t,r);
28056         while(r[i] < --qd) r.subTo(t,r);
28057       }
28058     }
28059     if(q != null) {
28060       r.drShiftTo(ys,q);
28061       if(ts != ms) BigInteger.ZERO.subTo(q,q);
28062     }
28063     r.t = ys;
28064     r.clamp();
28065     if(nsh > 0) r.rShiftTo(nsh,r);  // Denormalize remainder
28066     if(ts < 0) BigInteger.ZERO.subTo(r,r);
28067   }
28068   // (public) this mod a
28069   function bnMod(a) {
28070     var r = nbi();
28071     this.abs().divRemTo(a,null,r);
28072     if(this.s < 0 && r.compareTo(BigInteger.ZERO) > 0) a.subTo(r,r);
28073     return r;
28074   }
28075   // Modular reduction using "classic" algorithm
28076   function Classic(m) { this.m = m; }
28077   function cConvert(x) {
28078     if(x.s < 0 || x.compareTo(this.m) >= 0) return x.mod(this.m);
28079     else return x;
28080   }
28081   function cRevert(x) { return x; }
28082   function cReduce(x) { x.divRemTo(this.m,null,x); }
28083   function cMulTo(x,y,r) { x.multiplyTo(y,r); this.reduce(r); }
28084   function cSqrTo(x,r) { x.squareTo(r); this.reduce(r); }
28085   Classic.prototype.convert = cConvert;
28086   Classic.prototype.revert = cRevert;
28087   Classic.prototype.reduce = cReduce;
28088   Classic.prototype.mulTo = cMulTo;
28089   Classic.prototype.sqrTo = cSqrTo;
28090   // (protected) return "-1/this % 2^DB"; useful for Mont. reduction
28091   // justification:
28092   //         xy == 1 (mod m)
28093   //         xy =  1+km
28094   //   xy(2-xy) = (1+km)(1-km)
28095   // x[y(2-xy)] = 1-k^2m^2
28096   // x[y(2-xy)] == 1 (mod m^2)
28097   // if y is 1/x mod m, then y(2-xy) is 1/x mod m^2
28098   // should reduce x and y(2-xy) by m^2 at each step to keep size bounded.
28099   // JS multiply "overflows" differently from C/C++, so care is needed here.
28100   function bnpInvDigit() {
28101     if(this.t < 1) return 0;
28102     var x = this[0];
28103     if((x&1) == 0) return 0;
28104     var y = x&3;        // y == 1/x mod 2^2
28105     y = (y*(2-(x&0xf)*y))&0xf;  // y == 1/x mod 2^4
28106     y = (y*(2-(x&0xff)*y))&0xff;    // y == 1/x mod 2^8
28107     y = (y*(2-(((x&0xffff)*y)&0xffff)))&0xffff; // y == 1/x mod 2^16
28108     // last step - calculate inverse mod DV directly;
28109     // assumes 16 < DB <= 32 and assumes ability to handle 48-bit ints
28110     y = (y*(2-x*y%this.DV))%this.DV;        // y == 1/x mod 2^dbits
28111     // we really want the negative inverse, and -DV < y < DV
28112     return (y>0)?this.DV-y:-y;
28113   }
28114   // Montgomery reduction
28115   function Montgomery(m) {
28116     this.m = m;
28117     this.mp = m.invDigit();
28118     this.mpl = this.mp&0x7fff;
28119     this.mph = this.mp>>15;
28120     this.um = (1<<(m.DB-15))-1;
28121     this.mt2 = 2*m.t;
28122   }
28123   // xR mod m
28124   function montConvert(x) {
28125     var r = nbi();
28126     x.abs().dlShiftTo(this.m.t,r);
28127     r.divRemTo(this.m,null,r);
28128     if(x.s < 0 && r.compareTo(BigInteger.ZERO) > 0) this.m.subTo(r,r);
28129     return r;
28130   }
28131   // x/R mod m
28132   function montRevert(x) {
28133     var r = nbi();
28134     x.copyTo(r);
28135     this.reduce(r);
28136     return r;
28137   }
28138   // x = x/R mod m (HAC 14.32)
28139   function montReduce(x) {
28140     while(x.t <= this.mt2)  // pad x so am has enough room later
28141       x[x.t++] = 0;
28142     for(var i = 0; i < this.m.t; ++i) {
28143       // faster way of calculating u0 = x[i]*mp mod DV
28144       var j = x[i]&0x7fff;
28145       var u0 = (j*this.mpl+(((j*this.mph+(x[i]>>15)*this.mpl)&this.um)<<15))&x.DM;
28146       // use am to combine the multiply-shift-add into one call
28147       j = i+this.m.t;
28148       x[j] += this.m.am(0,u0,x,i,0,this.m.t);
28149       // propagate carry
28150       while(x[j] >= x.DV) { x[j] -= x.DV; x[++j]++; }
28151     }
28152     x.clamp();
28153     x.drShiftTo(this.m.t,x);
28154     if(x.compareTo(this.m) >= 0) x.subTo(this.m,x);
28155   }
28156   // r = "x^2/R mod m"; x != r
28157   function montSqrTo(x,r) { x.squareTo(r); this.reduce(r); }
28158   // r = "xy/R mod m"; x,y != r
28159   function montMulTo(x,y,r) { x.multiplyTo(y,r); this.reduce(r); }
28160   Montgomery.prototype.convert = montConvert;
28161   Montgomery.prototype.revert = montRevert;
28162   Montgomery.prototype.reduce = montReduce;
28163   Montgomery.prototype.mulTo = montMulTo;
28164   Montgomery.prototype.sqrTo = montSqrTo;
28165   // (protected) true iff this is even
28166   function bnpIsEven() { return ((this.t>0)?(this[0]&1):this.s) == 0; }
28167   // (protected) this^e, e < 2^32, doing sqr and mul with "r" (HAC 14.79)
28168   function bnpExp(e,z) {
28169     if(e > 0xffffffff || e < 1) return BigInteger.ONE;
28170     var r = nbi(), r2 = nbi(), g = z.convert(this), i = nbits(e)-1;
28171     g.copyTo(r);
28172     while(--i >= 0) {
28173       z.sqrTo(r,r2);
28174       if((e&(1<<i)) > 0) z.mulTo(r2,g,r);
28175       else { var t = r; r = r2; r2 = t; }
28176     }
28177     return z.revert(r);
28178   }
28179   // (public) this^e % m, 0 <= e < 2^32
28180   function bnModPowInt(e,m) {
28181     var z;
28182     if(e < 256 || m.isEven()) z = new Classic(m); else z = new Montgomery(m);
28183     return this.exp(e,z);
28184   }
28185   // protected
28186   BigInteger.prototype.copyTo = bnpCopyTo;
28187   BigInteger.prototype.fromInt = bnpFromInt;
28188   BigInteger.prototype.fromString = bnpFromString;
28189   BigInteger.prototype.clamp = bnpClamp;
28190   BigInteger.prototype.dlShiftTo = bnpDLShiftTo;
28191   BigInteger.prototype.drShiftTo = bnpDRShiftTo;
28192   BigInteger.prototype.lShiftTo = bnpLShiftTo;
28193   BigInteger.prototype.rShiftTo = bnpRShiftTo;
28194   BigInteger.prototype.subTo = bnpSubTo;
28195   BigInteger.prototype.multiplyTo = bnpMultiplyTo;
28196   BigInteger.prototype.squareTo = bnpSquareTo;
28197   BigInteger.prototype.divRemTo = bnpDivRemTo;
28198   BigInteger.prototype.invDigit = bnpInvDigit;
28199   BigInteger.prototype.isEven = bnpIsEven;
28200   BigInteger.prototype.exp = bnpExp;
28201   // public
28202   BigInteger.prototype.toString = bnToString;
28203   BigInteger.prototype.negate = bnNegate;
28204   BigInteger.prototype.abs = bnAbs;
28205   BigInteger.prototype.compareTo = bnCompareTo;
28206   BigInteger.prototype.bitLength = bnBitLength;
28207   BigInteger.prototype.mod = bnMod;
28208   BigInteger.prototype.modPowInt = bnModPowInt;
28209   // "constants"
28210   BigInteger.ZERO = nbv(0);
28211   BigInteger.ONE = nbv(1);
28212   // jsbn2 stuff
28213   // (protected) convert from radix string
28214   function bnpFromRadix(s,b) {
28215     this.fromInt(0);
28216     if(b == null) b = 10;
28217     var cs = this.chunkSize(b);
28218     var d = Math.pow(b,cs), mi = false, j = 0, w = 0;
28219     for(var i = 0; i < s.length; ++i) {
28220       var x = intAt(s,i);
28221       if(x < 0) {
28222         if(s.charAt(i) == "-" && this.signum() == 0) mi = true;
28223         continue;
28224       }
28225       w = b*w+x;
28226       if(++j >= cs) {
28227         this.dMultiply(d);
28228         this.dAddOffset(w,0);
28229         j = 0;
28230         w = 0;
28231       }
28232     }
28233     if(j > 0) {
28234       this.dMultiply(Math.pow(b,j));
28235       this.dAddOffset(w,0);
28236     }
28237     if(mi) BigInteger.ZERO.subTo(this,this);
28238   }
28239   // (protected) return x s.t. r^x < DV
28240   function bnpChunkSize(r) { return Math.floor(Math.LN2*this.DB/Math.log(r)); }
28241   // (public) 0 if this == 0, 1 if this > 0
28242   function bnSigNum() {
28243     if(this.s < 0) return -1;
28244     else if(this.t <= 0 || (this.t == 1 && this[0] <= 0)) return 0;
28245     else return 1;
28246   }
28247   // (protected) this *= n, this >= 0, 1 < n < DV
28248   function bnpDMultiply(n) {
28249     this[this.t] = this.am(0,n-1,this,0,0,this.t);
28250     ++this.t;
28251     this.clamp();
28252   }
28253   // (protected) this += n << w words, this >= 0
28254   function bnpDAddOffset(n,w) {
28255     if(n == 0) return;
28256     while(this.t <= w) this[this.t++] = 0;
28257     this[w] += n;
28258     while(this[w] >= this.DV) {
28259       this[w] -= this.DV;
28260       if(++w >= this.t) this[this.t++] = 0;
28261       ++this[w];
28262     }
28263   }
28264   // (protected) convert to radix string
28265   function bnpToRadix(b) {
28266     if(b == null) b = 10;
28267     if(this.signum() == 0 || b < 2 || b > 36) return "0";
28268     var cs = this.chunkSize(b);
28269     var a = Math.pow(b,cs);
28270     var d = nbv(a), y = nbi(), z = nbi(), r = "";
28271     this.divRemTo(d,y,z);
28272     while(y.signum() > 0) {
28273       r = (a+z.intValue()).toString(b).substr(1) + r;
28274       y.divRemTo(d,y,z);
28275     }
28276     return z.intValue().toString(b) + r;
28277   }
28278   // (public) return value as integer
28279   function bnIntValue() {
28280     if(this.s < 0) {
28281       if(this.t == 1) return this[0]-this.DV;
28282       else if(this.t == 0) return -1;
28283     }
28284     else if(this.t == 1) return this[0];
28285     else if(this.t == 0) return 0;
28286     // assumes 16 < DB < 32
28287     return ((this[1]&((1<<(32-this.DB))-1))<<this.DB)|this[0];
28288   }
28289   // (protected) r = this + a
28290   function bnpAddTo(a,r) {
28291     var i = 0, c = 0, m = Math.min(a.t,this.t);
28292     while(i < m) {
28293       c += this[i]+a[i];
28294       r[i++] = c&this.DM;
28295       c >>= this.DB;
28296     }
28297     if(a.t < this.t) {
28298       c += a.s;
28299       while(i < this.t) {
28300         c += this[i];
28301         r[i++] = c&this.DM;
28302         c >>= this.DB;
28303       }
28304       c += this.s;
28305     }
28306     else {
28307       c += this.s;
28308       while(i < a.t) {
28309         c += a[i];
28310         r[i++] = c&this.DM;
28311         c >>= this.DB;
28312       }
28313       c += a.s;
28314     }
28315     r.s = (c<0)?-1:0;
28316     if(c > 0) r[i++] = c;
28317     else if(c < -1) r[i++] = this.DV+c;
28318     r.t = i;
28319     r.clamp();
28320   }
28321   BigInteger.prototype.fromRadix = bnpFromRadix;
28322   BigInteger.prototype.chunkSize = bnpChunkSize;
28323   BigInteger.prototype.signum = bnSigNum;
28324   BigInteger.prototype.dMultiply = bnpDMultiply;
28325   BigInteger.prototype.dAddOffset = bnpDAddOffset;
28326   BigInteger.prototype.toRadix = bnpToRadix;
28327   BigInteger.prototype.intValue = bnIntValue;
28328   BigInteger.prototype.addTo = bnpAddTo;

28330   // Emscripten wrapper
28331   var Wrapper = {
28332     abs: function(l, h) {
28333       var x = new goog.math.Long(l, h);
28334       var ret;
28335       if (x.isNegative()) {
28336         ret = x.negate();
28337       } else {
28338         ret = x;
28339       }
28340       HEAP32[tempDoublePtr>>2] = ret.low_;
28341       HEAP32[tempDoublePtr+4>>2] = ret.high_;
28342     },
28343     ensureTemps: function() {
28344       if (Wrapper.ensuredTemps) return;
28345       Wrapper.ensuredTemps = true;
28346       Wrapper.two32 = new BigInteger();
28347       Wrapper.two32.fromString('4294967296', 10);
28348       Wrapper.two64 = new BigInteger();
28349       Wrapper.two64.fromString('18446744073709551616', 10);
28350       Wrapper.temp1 = new BigInteger();
28351       Wrapper.temp2 = new BigInteger();
28352     },
28353     lh2bignum: function(l, h) {
28354       var a = new BigInteger();
28355       a.fromString(h.toString(), 10);
28356       var b = new BigInteger();
28357       a.multiplyTo(Wrapper.two32, b);
28358       var c = new BigInteger();
28359       c.fromString(l.toString(), 10);
28360       var d = new BigInteger();
28361       c.addTo(b, d);
28362       return d;
28363     },
28364     stringify: function(l, h, unsigned) {
28365       var ret = new goog.math.Long(l, h).toString();
28366       if (unsigned && ret[0] == '-') {
28367         // unsign slowly using jsbn bignums
28368         Wrapper.ensureTemps();
28369         var bignum = new BigInteger();
28370         bignum.fromString(ret, 10);
28371         ret = new BigInteger();
28372         Wrapper.two64.addTo(bignum, ret);
28373         ret = ret.toString(10);
28374       }
28375       return ret;
28376     },
28377     fromString: function(str, base, min, max, unsigned) {
28378       Wrapper.ensureTemps();
28379       var bignum = new BigInteger();
28380       bignum.fromString(str, base);
28381       var bigmin = new BigInteger();
28382       bigmin.fromString(min, 10);
28383       var bigmax = new BigInteger();
28384       bigmax.fromString(max, 10);
28385       if (unsigned && bignum.compareTo(BigInteger.ZERO) < 0) {
28386         var temp = new BigInteger();
28387         bignum.addTo(Wrapper.two64, temp);
28388         bignum = temp;
28389       }
28390       var error = false;
28391       if (bignum.compareTo(bigmin) < 0) {
28392         bignum = bigmin;
28393         error = true;
28394       } else if (bignum.compareTo(bigmax) > 0) {
28395         bignum = bigmax;
28396         error = true;
28397       }
28398       var ret = goog.math.Long.fromString(bignum.toString()); // min-max checks should have clamped this to a range goog.math.Long can handle well
28399       HEAP32[tempDoublePtr>>2] = ret.low_;
28400       HEAP32[tempDoublePtr+4>>2] = ret.high_;
28401       if (error) throw 'range error';
28402     }
28403   };
28404   return Wrapper;
